At least 25 other people were wounded in the bombing.
column5: Tolo TV, Kabul, Tolo News, Kabul, Voice of Jihad website in Pashto 20 Jan 16

column63: Burundian singer Pascal Tresor Nshimirimana was killed yesterday [3 January] when he was shot in the back by police. Popularly known as Lissouba, the 27 year old leader of a citizen movement was found dead in Musaga.
At least 29 people, including 10 foreigners, were killed in an Al-Qaeda attack on a top hotel in Burkina Faso's capital Ouagadougou. At least 54 were wounded.
Two female suicide bombers have killed at least 12 people and injured 11 at a mosque in the village of Kouyape, in Kolofata district on Cameroon's northern border with Nigeria
At least three female suicide bombers targeting markets Bodo town in northern Cameroon killed 32 people and wounded 68 on Monday
column67: Radio France Internationale, Paris, Daily Trust, The Guardian

column28: Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Rwanda (FDLR)
column63: Rwandan Hutu rebels killed 14 civilians from a rival ethnic Nande group in the town of Miriki in North Kivu province in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo early on Thursday morning and wounded nine, the army said

Five people, including a child, were executed at a New Year's gathering in El Salvador early on Friday. A group of men dressed in dark, military-style garb and armed with assault rifles broke into two homes during New Year's parties and killed five people, including a woman and a child, in Los Cerritos, 160 km east of the capital, according to a police spokesman. The massacre may be gang related, since the neighborhood is controlled by the Mara Salvatrucha
column72: Reuters identifies the location as San Miguel, a nearby large city, but Los Cerritos seems more specific.

column63: Over 20 people were killed in tribal clashes in Gambela Regional State [in western Ethiopia]. Several others sustained injuries in the clashes. According to information obtained from Gambela Regional State, misunderstandings among individuals turned tribal, pitting the Nuer against the Anyuak communities.

At least seven people were killed and scores were injured yesterday in Gambella town, south of Ethiopia, during an attempted prison break. Eye witnesses told Addis Standard that a fierce clash between the Nuer and Anywaa ethnic groups also left scores wounded when hundreds of Nuers attacked a prison called Gambella regional state correctional facility.
column72: Not clear exactly who was targeted or circumstances of the killings

column63: A fight at an overcrowded Guatemalan prison killed at least eight prisoners and wounded 20, the country's interior minister said on Friday. An altercation between two inmates turned into a battle between rival gangs at the prison in Puerto Barrios, about 185 miles (300 km) northeast of the capital, said Interior Minister Eunice Mendizabal.
A battle between rival gangs in an overcrowded prison in the town of Chimaltenago near Guatemala's capital left six inmates dead and another six wounded, officials said Tuesday.

Police spokesman told local media that six men were killed by unknown gunmen in a house in the town of Tejeras in central Comayagua province early on Sunday morning. Authorities said narcotics trafficking appeared to be involved.
column72: Geonames has no Tejeras anywhere in Comayagua province but Google Maps shows a ""Las Tierras"" in the middle of the province so I used those coordinates

column63: Sixteen people have been killed in an explosive-device blast in Al-Jam'iyyah neighbourhood in the [Iraqi] city of Al-Ramadi
A muezzin -- the person appointed to recite the Muslim call to prayer -- was shot dead near his home in Iskandariyah , police and medics said.
The Islamic State militant group has executed 83 men who belong to Al-Jabur tribe in Nineveh Province, private pro-Shi'i Buratha News website reported on 5 January.
column72: No location given except province, so the coordinates are the approximate centroid the province as a whole

column39: local security personnel, lawyers and election officials
column63: According to Buratha News, IS shot dead more than 100 people in Mosul who used to work as local security personnel, lawyers and election officials in Nineveh Province.
Islamic State gunmen attacked a shopping mall in eastern Baghdad on Monday evening, killing at least 12 civilians and wounding at least 40. ISIS claimed responsibility for the attack.
column67: Al-Jazeera TV, Doha, Al-Mada website, Baghdad

column63: At least 20 people were killed and 50 others wounded in a car bombing followed by a suicide bombing inside a casino in the town of Muqdadiya in eastern Iraq, security and medical sources said. ISIS claimed responsibility for the attack.

At least seven people were killed and at least 15 wounded when a suicide bomber driving a car attacked a commercial street in the southeastern Baghdad suburb of Nahrawan on Monday, police and medical sources said. ISIS claimed responsibility for the attack.

At least 15 Agatu farmers were killed in Udeni Ruwa District in Toto Local Government Area of Nasarawa State after an attack on two of its communities by Fulani gunmen early Sunday, January 3, 2016. The raid may have been in retaliation for an earlier killing of a herdsman and some cattle by Agatu youth.

column13: Izge Gwoza and Izge Dambuwa villages
column63: At least five persons were killed on Monday [4 January] and many others in Izge Gwoza and Izge Dambuwa villages in the reclaimed Gwoza town in Borno State as suicide bomber sneaked into a resettling members of a recently displaced community, witnesses and security sources said. Two more people were killed by Boko Haram gunmen on bicycles
column67: Daily Independent, Leadership website, Abuja, Vanguard

column63: Boko Haram insurgents have killed seven residents of Madagali Local Government of Adamawa State during a midnight attack while eight others escaped with injuries, residents and security officials reported.

Five persons were killed and five others injured in a cult clash in Ikorodu, Lagos on Tuesday. The fight between the Aye (Black Axe) and Eiye confraternities was said to have started around 1am during Itunmeko street carnival.

Cameroonian troops pursuing Boko Haram fired rocket-propelled grenades indiscriminately that killed a family of four, then shot and killed two other civilians in the town of Ashigashiya, Borno State, Nigerian villagers said Tuesday. Reports indicate that this is part of apparent attempt by Cameroon to create a no-go zone along the border where troops could shoot anything that moved.

Eight members of the Indigenous People of Biafra [IPOB], were allegedly shot dead by the military in Aba in Abia State during their peaceful protest over the continued detention of their leader, Nnamdi Kanu, according to the spokesman of IPOB. At least 30 people were injured by bullets.

The kidnapped king of Ubulu-Uku Kingdom in Aniocha North Local Government Area of Delta State, HRM Obi Akaeze Ofulue III, has been reportedly killed by his abductors. The deceased king was on January 5, abducted by suspected Fulani herdsmen on Obior/ Igbodo Road, Delta State, along with his driver.
No fewer than 16 persons have been reportedly shot dead in Ula Upata community, Ahoada East Local Government Area of Rivers State, by suspected gang members.

column13: Demsare, Wunamokoh, Dikajam and Taboungo villages
column63: The Divisional Police Officer, DPO, in charge of Vunokilang Police Station in Girei Local Government Area of Adamawa State was among the 30 people killed in an attack by suspected Fulani herdsmen on Sunday morning . The suspected herdsmen raided four villages: Demsare, Wunamokoh, Dikajam and Taboungo in what is believed to be a vengeance mission over an existing feud with farmers in the area.
column72: DPO was part of a police ``team'' that was ambushed, so unclear how many of dead were police.

column63: At least 40 villagers in Gwadale border community under Gwoza local government area of Borno state were feared killed on Monday as soldiers of the Cameroonian national allegedly opened fire on fleeing Boko Haram believed to have ran over to Nigeria, witnesses said. Cameroon is denying reports
At least 16 people were killed and 30 others injured Wednesday in three suicide blasts in the northeast Nigerian town of Chibok
column65: AFP, Reuters, CNN, NYT, BBC, All Africa, AP
column67: Leadership website, Abuja, Daily Trust, Deutsche Welle, Daily Independent

column63: A teenage suicide bomber on Friday blew himself up in a grain market in Gombe in Adawama state, killing at least 11 people and wounding 58, witnesses and medical officials said.
column67: Daily Trust website, Abuja, Premium Times

column63: At least 85 people were killed Saturday night when Boko Haram militants attacked three villages on the outskirts of Maiduguri, Borno state. The victims include women and children while over 100 people were also injured in the attack.
column65: Reuters, AFP, CNN, All Africa, NYT
column67: Premium Times, The Guardian, Daily Independent, Leadership, Vanguard, Daily Trust

column63: A suicide bomber rammed his motorcycle into a police vehicle next to the roadside checkpoint on the border of Peshawar in northwestern Pakistan on Tuesday, killing at least 5 civilians and wounding more than 20, officials said. The Taliban claimed responsibility for the attack.
column67: Geo News TV, Karachi, Dawn website, Karachi
column72: At least five police also killed; wounded total probably includes some police

column63: Gunmen killed 19 students and wounded at least 30 other people in an attack on Bacha Khan University in Charsadda, Peshawar. A breakaway Taliban faction claimed responsibility; the mainstream Taliban denied involvement.

column29: Arab Beni Halba tribe and Masalit tribe?
column37: Arab Beni Halba tribe and Masalit tribe?
column63: At least 14 people have been killed and ten wounded in unrest in Sudan's West Darfur, sources said Monday, the day after security forces dispersed protesters outside government buildings in the state capital Geneina.
column72: Appears to be related to ethnic conflict between Arab Beni Halba tribe and Masalit tribe though details are confusing, even for Sudan

column63: At least 10 people have been killed and more than 30 others injured in renewed clashes between clan militias in Buq-garsor, some 50km west of Beled Weyne, the capital of Hiiraan region in central Somalia.
column67: Radio Kulmiye website, Mogadishu, Shabelle Media Network website, Mogadishu, Shabelle Media Network

column13: Kurtun-Dhoole, Warta Adan Jibril and Ey Kumoogle
column63: Seven people have been killed after Kenyan fighter jets reportedly bombed residential areas in Kurtun-Dhoole, Warta Adan Jibril and Ey Kumoogle in south of Somalia's Gedo region, witness and elders said.
column67: Shabelle Media Network, Shabelle Media Network website, Mogadishu
column72: Could not geolocate any of those names; coordinates for arbitrary location in southern Gedo region

column63: At least 17 people have been killed in an attack on a beachside restaurant in the Somali capital. The al Qaeda-linked group al-Shabab took responsibility for the siege.
column67: Shabelle Media Network, Deutsche Welle, Daily Trust

column63: The Kenyan army have "killed the commissioner of Ceel Adde District in Likooleey area" in southwestern Somalia, reports privately-owned Shabeelle website on 27 January. A Somali government official confirmed the killing; the Kenyan army had no comment.
column72: Kenya army seems to be engaged in revenge attacks in the Ceel Adde area following an al-Shabaab attack which al-Shabaab claims killed 100 Kenya soldiers. Exact date of killing unclear.

column63: Turkish army tank shelling and artillery bombardment have killed 12 Kurdish civilians in the Zap district of the city of Silopi southeast of the country, the Patriotic Union of Kurdistan (PUK)-funded SNN website reported on 5 January.
column67: Patriotic Union of Kurdistan (PUK) media website in Sorani Kurdish 5 Jan 16

column63: Turkish soldiers have killed 31 Kurdish civilians in the "besieged" Kurdish city of Cizre southeast Turkey on 6 January, the pro-Kurdistan Democratic Party (KDP) Rudaw news portal reported on the same day.
Ten people were killed and 15 wounded in a suspected terrorist attack on Tuesday in the main tourist hub of Turkey's largest city Istanbul, officials said.

Kurdish PKK militants have attacked a police station in the town of Cinar in southeast Turkey with a truck bomb, killing five civilians including a baby and two toddlers. At least 39 people were wounded. The PKK later apologized for killing the children.
column67: Anadolu (also known as Anatolia) news agency website, Ankara

column63: Gunmen killed a prominent ally of Venezuelan President Nicolas Maduro in Caracas, prosecutors said on Wednesday, a crime the socialist leader suggested was politically motivated.
column72: Might have been a robbery: accounts differed

column63: Suspected Islamic State group jihadists also shot dead Sheikh Ali Othman, a Sufi imam who was considered a moderate, in the city, according to security officials.

At least 15 Yemeni civilians were killed and 25 wounded in an air strike by a Saudi-led military coalition near the village of Bilad al-Rus, around 40 km (25 miles) south of Sanaa, residents said on Wednesday
On Sunday, 9 civilians were killed and 10 wounded when a suicide car bomb exploded outside the home of the director of security for the port city of Aden, eyewitnesses and medics said.

Air strikes by Saudi-led warplanes on northern Yemen have killed six people in the village of Dhahyan, including an ambulance driver working for Doctors Without Borders (MSF), and wounded 40 others, the relief agency said Friday.
A Saudi-led coalition air strike killed a Yemeni judge allied with the Houthis and seven members of his family in the capital Sanaa on Sunday, residents said. Five other family members were injured.
column72: Saudis claim targeting wasn't deliberate, and Saudi bombs frequently hit a mile or more from their targets, so this is probably correct

column63: A suicide bombing killed seven people and wounded seven others Friday night in Aden, medics and security sources said.
Airstrikes by a Saudi-led coalition targeting Yemen's Shiite rebels killed at least 8 civilian overnight in the capital, Sanaa, officials said on Saturday.

At least seven people were killed yesterday in Gambella town, south of Ethiopia, during an attempted prison break. Eye witnesses told Addis Standard that a fierce clash between the Nuer and Anywaa ethnic groups also left scores wounded when hundreds of Nuers attacked a prison called Gambella regional state correctional facility.

Governor Samuel Ortom of Benue state yesterday condemned the renewed hostilities between suspected Fulani herdsmen and farmers in Agatu local government area which resulted in the death of seven persons.
column72: No information on how many killed in each group

column63: A Taliban suicide bomber blew himself after joining a queue to enter a police office in Kabul on Monday, killing 20 people and wounding at least 29. The Taliban claimed responsibility for the attack.
column67: Ariana News TV, Kabul, Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column36: secretary of the acting governor of Konduz Province
column63: The secretary of the acting governor of northern Konduz Province has been killed by unknown gunmen.
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column63: Six civilians were killed and nine others injured in the explosion in front of a bakery in the main bazaar of Yahyakhel District at around 1200 local time in Paktika Province [eastern Afghanistan].
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column63: At least six members of a family, including four children, were killed in a mine explosion in Waza Khwa District of [eastern] Paktika Province.
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

At least six civilians were killed and over 30 injured Wednesday in a double suicide attack by two female bombers during a funeral wake in the village of Nguetchewe in Cameroon's northern border region.
Two female suicide bombers posing as food vendors killed at least 24 people and injured 112 others in a market in Meme, northern Cameroon, security sources said on Friday.

At least 21 people were killed, 40 wounded and dozens of houses burned in clashes between militias aligned with the Nande and Hutu ethnic groups in the Tama area southwest of Lubero Territory to the north of Goma town in Nord Kivu Province [eastern DRCongo]eastern Democratic Republic of Congo, the United Nations said on Monday, expressing alarm at rising ethnic violence. U.N. spokesman Amouzoun Codjo Martin said the weekend attacks were carried out by members of two militias, the Nande-dominated UPDI and the NDC, which is mostly made up of Nyanga, another local ethnic group.
column72: Reports are fragmentary and while clearly both civilians and combatants have been killed, it isn't clear how many are combatants.

column63: Six people have been killed and 14 others kidnapped by suspected Ugandan ADF [Allied Democratic Forces] rebel fighters while about 30 houses have been torched. column63: A journalist was shot and killed at point-blank range at the headquarters of the Union of Democratic Forces of Guinea (UFDG) in the capital Conakry. in Guinea on Friday during clashes between rival factions of the West African nation's main opposition party, witnesses and the government said.

Twenty eight people were killed during three days of the Jat quota agitation in the North Indian state of Haryana, Director General of Police Yashapl Singhal said. Over 200 persons including few security personnel were also injured during the agitation.
Iraqi medical and security officials say a string of roadside bombs and a shooting have left nine people dead and 33 wounded across the capital.

Suicide bombers hit a Shiite religious building and a military checkpoint in a Shiite-majority neighborhood of Baghdad Thursday, killing 12 civilians and wounding 48, an Iraqi security official said. The Islamic State group claimed responsibility for the attacks.
Some 40 people were killed and dozens others injured when a suicide bomber blew himself up in a mourning ceremony in Al-Miqdadiyah district of Diyala Province
A twin suicide bombing claimed by Islamic State killed 73 people and wounded more than 100 in a Shi'ite district of Baghdad

column63: Unidentified planes carried out air strikes early on Friday morning in the western Libyan city of Sabratha, killing 41 people and wounding 6, the city's mayor said.
Forty-nine people were killed and twelve people were wounded in a prison riot at the Topo Chico prison in Monterrey in the northeastern Mexican state of Nuevo Leon

Gunmen ambushed a packed pick-up truck in northwestern Mexico, killing nine men and four women in a region plagued by drug cartel violence, authorities said Sunday.The attack took place on Saturday in a rural community of the municipality of San Ignacio at the border of the states of Sinaloa and Durango, prosecutors said.
At least 10 people were killed in the northern Menaka district in Mali in the last week in reprisal killings over the murder of a tribal elder, officials told AFP on Tuesday.

Two female suicide bombers Tuesday detonated bombs at the Internally Displaced Persons (IDP) camp in Dikwa, Borno State, leaving 58 people dead and over 78 others injured.

On the morning of 22 March 2016, three coordinated nail bombings occurred in Belgium: two at Brussels Airport in Zaventem, and one at Maalbeek metro station in Brussels. Armed men killed 12 people in villages in Central African Republic, local officials said on Sunday. The attacks took place near the central town of Bambari and were likely linked to livestock rustling or an inter-ethnic dispute involving the Peuhl, or Fulani, ethnic group, the officials said.

At least 16 prisoners died and eight were injured in a fire Thursday as they protested overcrowding and other issues inside a prison in the capital of the South American country of Guyana, authorities said.

Honduran indigenous activist Bertha Caceres, a respected environmentalist who won the prestigious Goldman Prize last year for her outspoken advocacy, was murdered in her home in La Esperanza, Honduras Thursday, her family said.

Authorities say that assailants armed with AK-47 assault rifles burst into a pool hall controlled by the Barrio 18 gang in Honduras' capital and opened fire, killing at least 12 people and wounding three others.

ISIS claimed responsibility, according to a statement posted online by supporters.

Iraqi officials say a suicide bombing in the capital has killed at least seven civilians and wounded 23. A police officer says the suicide bomber set off his payload among a group of day laborers in Baghdad's Tayaran Square on Tuesday. The Islamic State group claimed the attack in an online statement circulated by supporters.

Five people were found burned to death in a van on a remote stretch of road outside Colombo, their bodies too charred to be easily identified. "This looks like some kind of revenge attack [by gangs]," a senior police official told AFP.
No fewer than five persons were killed yesterday in an ethnic clash between Hausa and Yoruba traders at the popular Mile 12 area of Lagos that also left scores with varying degrees of injuries.

The Chief Priest (Ohen-Ogba) of Aruogba in Oredo Local Government Area of Edo State , 81-year-old Pa Clifford Omosomwan, in by unknown assailants. The victim had been involved in mediating a political struggle for the leadership of the Community Development Association (CDA)

Fourteen civilians were killed and at least 23 injured Monday morning when a bomber detonated his suicide vest after shooting his way into a court compound in the town of Shabqadar about 20 miles north of Peshawar, a senior police official said. The Taliban claimed responsibility for the attack.
A powerful bomb ripped through a bus carrying government employees in Peshawar, killing at least 15 people and leaving 25 severely injured.
column65: AFP, BBC, AP, CNN, Reuters, NYT

column63: At least 72 people were killed and more than 300 injured when a suicide bomb ripped through the parking space of a crowded park in Lahore where Christians were celebrating Easter Sunday, officials said. The Taliban faction Jamaat-ul-Ahrar has claimed responsibility for the attack.

Seven people were killed and 20 others injured in attacks by army forces and allied militiamen on areas in the southern part of Jebel Marra on Saturday. Ten villages northwest of Kalokiting burned to ashes, making about 30,000 villagers homeless, a listener told Radio Dabanga from Koni, north of Kalokiting.

column63: Six people, two Turkish nationals and four Somalis, were confirmed killed in Mogadishu today after gunmen opened fire on a vehicle carrying Turkish-run Deva [Education and Research] Hospital's workers and [medical] teachers. Six Turkish and Kenyan nationals were also wounded in the attack.

A suicide bombing at a cafe near a hotel in the town of Galkayo in central Somalia killed at least nine people and wounded 10 others, a police official said Thursday. Al-Shabab claimed responsibility for the attack, saying it targeted officials from Puntland.

A Muslim village headman was shot and killed by insurgents in Narathiwat's Si Sakhon district Tuesday [8 March]. Police said Abdulroseh Jeha, 48 was riding his motorcycle to visit a suspected insurgent to tell him to surrender, when he was ambushed and gunned down.
Seven civilians were killed Monday when Islamist fighters attacked army and police barracks in the Tunisian town of Ben Guerdan, the government said.
column72: Civilians seem to have been killed in crossfire, but made Islamists the perpetrator since they initiated the attack.

column63: Fighting in western Uganda between supporters of rival candidates involved in last month's national and local elections has killed 22 people and wounded 10 others in recent days, police said. column63: The body of a lawyer representing one of two Russian servicemen on trial in Ukraine has been found buried in an abandoned farm, officials said Friday. According to Anatoly Matios, chief military prosecutor, a suspect in the murder said Yuri Grabovsky was drugged and kidnapped in Kiev earlier this month, then taken to the Black Sea port of Odessa, before he was transferred to the countryside nearly 150 kilometers (93 miles) south of the capital where he was shot and killed.
column72: Exact date of kidnapping and death not given in article

column63: A group of gunmen attacked and killed 28 miners in a recently opened small goldmine near Tumerero in Bolivar state in southeastern Venezuela. Witnesses say gunmen descended on the mine, rounded up the 28 miners, killed them execution style, then hacked up their bodies and hauled them away in a truck.
column72: Story developed gradually over the month, and about 20 of the bodies were recovered from a mass grave. All accounts are consistent with 28 total deaths; there are numerous accusations that the government is involved but the government denies these.

column63: Gunmen in the southern Yemen city of Aden on Friday stormed a retirement home run by a charity established by Mother Teresa, killing 16 people, including four Catholic nuns, officials and witnesses said.
At least six civilians were killed on Friday as Yemeni pro-government forces gained ground around third city Taez which has been under rebel siege for several months, officials said.
At least 106 civilians were killed and 47 injured when three Saudi airstrikes attacked attacked the center of Khamees Market in Mustaba'a, Hajjah, northern Yemen according to UNICEF.
column72: Quite an assortment of numbers reported since many bodies were not intact; the UNICEF figure is a later one. One local tribal leader aligned with the Houthis, said 33 of the dead were fighters, but no other reports support this.

column63: 14 civilians, have been killed in two days of fighting between pro-government forces and Shiite Huthi rebels on the outskirts of Taiz in Yemen, officials said Sunday

Snipers with the Iran-backed rebels have shot dead a cameraman who was covering clashes in Taiz, the country's union of journalists said on Tuesday. Three other cameramen were wounded in the gunfire, the statement added.

A triple suicide bombing on checkpoint outside a Saudi-led coalition military camp near Aden in southern Yemen killed 22 people Friday, including civilians, witnesses and medical officials said. The Islamic State affiliate claimed responsibility for the attacks in a short statement carrying the name of the group's news agency, Amaq.
column72: No breakdown of civilian vs combatant casualties but the civilian casualties appear to have been substantial

column63: A suicide bomber on a motorcycle killed at least six civilians and wounded 22 Tuesday when he detonated near a clinic and a school in Charikar in Parwan province during a police chase in eastern Afghanistan, officials said.
Two people were killed and seven wounded when a mini-bus carrying workers from Afghanistan's Ministry of Education was hit by a bomb blast in the capital on Monday, the ministry said.

Following extensive fighting in Konduz, The head of Konduz provincial hospital, Dr Mohammad Na'im Manghal, told Afghan Islamic Press [AIP] that since yesterday until this morning, 16 April, five dead bodies and 85 injured individuals were taken to the hospital. He said all the deaths were children. There are security forces, women and children among the wounded individuals.

column72: Wounded is estimate for civilians

column63: Afghan government confirms 64 people were killed in suicide truck bomb explosion and subsequent firefight in Kabul and 347 were wounded. The Taliban have claimed responsibility

Officials in Burundi say at least five people were killed and six injured when gunmen opened fire on a market Monday eveningin the eastern city of Gisuru. The attackers are believed to be connected to a group of exiles in Tanzania led by Leonidas Hatungimana, a former presidential spokesman who was sacked last year after he advised Nkurunziza not to seek a third term.

A official from Burundi's ruling party was shot dead in what appeared the latest in a spate of tit-for-tat killings. Phocas Bakaza, a member of the CNDD-FDD party in Mutimbuza area near the capital Bujumbura, was killed late on Wednesday
column72: Could not geolocate Mutimbuza; coordinates are for Bujumbura

column63: Five people were killed and three others wounded in a gun and grenade attack in a district of Burundi's capital which is stronghold of opposition to President Pierre Nkurunziza, police said.

column63: The Islamic State group claimed responsibility for the hacking to death of a university professor in the city of Rajshahi in Bangladesh on Saturday, accusing him of calling for atheism.

The Bangladeshi branch of al-Qaida claimed responsibility Tuesday for the killing of a gay rights activist and his friend, who were hacked to death on Monday in their apartment in the capital Dhaka by a group of assailants posing as couriers.

A rebel coalition operating in eastern DRCongo knnown as Nyatura FDLR (Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Rwanda rebel coalition) has killed the traditional leader of Zanganano village in Boshimo, Bashali Mokoto grouping, Masisi territory, 20 kilometers from Pinga in Walikale territory, Goma-based UN sponsored Radio Okapi reported on 4 April.

column67: Addis Standard, Ethiopian Broadcasting Corporation TV (formerly ETV), Addis Ababa, Al Jazeera

column63: Clashes between the Anuak and Neur ethnic groups in and around Gambella in west Ethiopia have left 14 dead, security and NGO sources reported. The clash was triggered when an Anuak driver of an NGO car ran over and killed two children from the Nuer ethnic group in a camp for South Sudanese refugees.

A Gambian opposition leader and two other members of his party were tortured to death in a prison following their arrest last week at a protest in Banjul. Two female members of the party are said to be in a coma.

in the southern province of Dhi Qar (also known as Nasiriyah) when a suicide bomber blew himself up inside a restaurant that is frequented by Shiite paramilitary militia fighters, killing at least 14 people. A suicide attack claimed by the Islamic State group killed at least eight people at a Shiite mosque on the southwestern edge of Baghdad on Friday, security and medical officials said. The blast, which occurred shortly after Friday prayers, also wounded at least 33 people, the officials said.
At least nine people were killed on Saturday when a suicide attacker detonated a car bomb at a security checkpoint in northern Baghdad, police sources said
A car bomb exploded in a predominantly Shi'ite district of eastern Baghdad on Monday, killing at least 11 people and wounding 39 others, security and medical sources said
Sources to Al-Jazeera TV: Five civilians have been killed, including a child, in Iraqi army bombardment of Fallujah and its vicinity

The Islamic State group claimed responsibility for a bombing Saturday in a market in the predominantly Shia town of Nahrawan east of Baghdad, according to a statement posted on an IS-affiliated website. The attack killed at least 21 people and wounded at least 42 others, according to Iraqi police and hospital officials.

Four persons including the All Progressives Congress, APC, youth leader, were feared killed in another bloody clash between Fulani herdsmen and farmers at Tse Tia, in Tarka Local Government area of Benue State. Youth from the village first killed two Fulani whose cattle were grazing on village land, then Fulani responded by kidnapping and killing the APC leader and another man.
Suspected Boko Haram militants on horseback attacked Gurum and Dokshi villages in Gulani LGA ""They burnt them completely and killed more than 20 residents.""

Suspected ethnic Fulani herders killed at least 15 villagers and burnt down homes in Taraba state in eastern Nigeria in a dispute over grazing rights, police said on Wednesday. State police spokesman Kwaji Joseph told AFP the incident happened on Sunday when the herdsmen stormed Dori and Mesuma in the Gashaka local government area.

column63: The traditional leader of Bambu area has been killed in his locality situated some 100 kilometres north of Goma in Rutshuru Territory, Nord Kivu Province. Many sources contacted on the ground said Kambere Luanda Bonane was shot dead at his home at about 1930 local time by unidentified armed men, who left without taking anything.
Officials in Badghis Province [western Afghanistan] say that five civilians were killed and five others injured in a mine explosion targeting a civilian vehicle in Qades District of Badghis Province
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column63: Eleven people, including two children, were killed and 23 others were wounded as a result of a suicide attack in front of a militia commander in Nazian District of [eastern] Nangarhar Province today.
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column63: Unidentified armed motorcyclists have attacked and killed a tribal elder in Farah city in Farah Province on Wednesday [18 May].
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column63: Six civilians have been killed and three others wounded as a result of a night raid on a house by Afghan military forces in the Amir Khelo area of Pol-e Khomri, capital of [northern] Baghlan Province.
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column63: Gunmen have shot dead a retired judge in the Qala Cha area of the eighth security precinct of the Kabul city, private Pakistan-based Afghan Islamic Press news agency reported on 20 May.
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column63: Spokesman for Kandahar governor Samim Khpalwak told Afghan Islamic Press [AIP] that unidentified armed motorcyclist shot and killed Hedayatollah Sofowal, a tribal elder today before noon in Ayno Mena in 12th Precinct of Kandahar city.
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column63: An Afghan official says at least five civilians were killed when their vehicle hit a roadside bomb in Shah Wali Kot district in southern Kandahar province.

The head of Helmand civil society, Sardar Mohammad Hamdard, told Afghan Islamic Press [AIP] on Tuesday that they have recently received information from the people of the area that they had sustained casualties in the operation which started in Marja District yesterday. He added: "Eight people had been martyred and some others lost their body parts during the operation."
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column63: A suicide bomber targeted a minibus carrying court employees in Kabul during morning rush hour Wednesday, killing 11 people and wounding 4, Afghan and UN officials said. The Taliban claimed responsibility for the attack.

The Taliban kidnapped 190 passengers from different inter-city buses in Angor Bagh area of the Aliabab district of Konduz Province and killed 9 of the passengers, who were apparently government employees.
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar, Ariana TV, Kabul, Afghan Channel One (1TV), Kabul
column72: No claim of responsibility from the Taliban

column63: A local Sufi Muslim leader has been found hacked to death in Rajshahi district in Bangladesh in a suspected Islamist killing, police said Saturday
column72: No geographical details beyond "Rajshahi district", which is a pretty large place (2.5M population).

column63: Unidentified attackers killed an elderly Buddhist monk in Naikkhangchhari upazila of Bandarban in Chittagong province.

ISIS claimed responsibility for the death of a Bangladeshi doctor killed by machete-wielding attackers in Kushtia district, saying that he was promoting Christianity. A friend of the victim was seriously wounded in the attack. Police say the doctor was actually a follower of the 19th century Bengali secularist Lalon Shah.

column28: Allied Democratic Forces National Army for the Liberation of Uganda
column63: At least 17 people were last night killed by suspected ADF NALU [Allied Democratic Forces National Army for the Liberation of Uganda] in Minibo and Mutsonge, two suburbs of Baungatsho Luna locality, at least 60km northeast of Beni territory.
column72: Could not geolocate any of the place names so location is just arbitrary point NE of Beni

column11: border of Nord Kivu and Ituri provinces
column28: Allied Democratic Forces National Army for the Liberation of Uganda
column63: Five civilians have been killed and houses torched in an attack perpetrated by suspected ADF NALU [Allied Democratic Forces National Army for the Liberation of Uganda] rebel combatants in Ndalia and Kata Beyi, two villages situated at the limit between Nord Kivu and Itur provinces.
column72: Could not geolocate either village; coordinates are for arbitrary location along the provincial border near Uganda

column63: At least eight Afghan nationals were killed and 20 others wounded after Iranian border guards opened fire on them. According to reports, a vehicle carrying the Afghan nationals tried to enter Iranian soil illegally in Rafsanjan area of that country and the driver did not pay attention to the stop warning of the Iranian border forces
column72: Rafsanjan (Kerman) is nowhere even remotely close to the Afghan border, so something is off here: I've geolocated this on the border where one might be traveling to Rafsanjan but that's probably not where the incident occurred.

column63: Two suicide car bombs claimed by Islamic State killed at least 32 people and wounded 75 others in the center of the southern Iraqi city of Samawa on Sunday, police and medics said.

An explosives-laden car detonated on Monday in the Iraqi capital, killing at least 18 Shiite pilgrims who were commemorating the anniversary of the death of a revered imam, officials said. At least 45 people were wounded in the attack. Shortly after the explosion, the Sunni extremist Islamic State group claimed responsibility for the attack in an online statement.

A bomb went off in a graveyard in the town of Haswa south of Baghdad Thursday, killing five people among a group of mourners at a burial, Iraq's interior ministry spokesman said. Fourteen people were wounded in the attack.

A car bomb claimed by Islamic State in the eastern Iraqi city of Baquba killed at least 16 people on Monday and wounded 54 others near a bakery close to the city center, police and hospital sources said.

Three suicide bombings claimed by Islamic State in Shia neighborhoods across Baghdad killed at least 92 people on Wednesday and wounded at least 118, Iraqi police and hospital sources said, in the deadliest attacks in the Iraqi capital this year.
column65: AP, BBC, Reuters, CNN, AFP, NYT
column67: Al-Jazeera TV, Doha, Rudaw website, Arbil, Al-Mada website, Baghdad

column63: A dawn attack on the gas plant in the town of Taji began with a suicide car bombing at the facility's main gate, then several suicide bombers and militants then broke into the plant and clashed with security forces. The dead included six civilians and eight security forces; 27 troops were wounded.
column72: Other stories reported only 4 civilians killed

column63: A car bomb at a shopping area in the town of Latifiyah, about 20 miles (30 kilometers) south of the capital, killed seven people, including two soldiers, police and medical officials said. Eighteen people were wounded in the attack, four of whom were soldiers.
In Baghdad, three separate bomb attacks targeted commercial areas, killing at least eight civilians and wounding 28 others, police and medical officials said.

At least 77 people were killed and more than 140 wounded by three bombings, at least one a suicide bombing, in Shia neighborhoods in Baghdad, including Sadr City, on Tuesday. The Islamic State claimed responsibility for one of the attacks.
column67: Al-Arabiya TV, Dubai, Al-Mada website, Baghdad

column63: More than 20 people were killed and about 50 injured in three bombings, including two suicide attacks, that hit Baghdad on Monday, police and medical sources said. There were no immediate claims of responsibility.
column67: Rudaw website, Arbil, Al-Jazeera TV, Doha

column63: A suicide bomber blew himself up on Sunday among young Iraqis assembled in a cafe in Moqdadiyah, northeast of Baghdad, killing at least seven people and wounding 22, police and hospital officials said. The Islamic State group said it carried out the attack.

An opposition leader says a businessman who was critical of President Uhuru Kenyatta's government was shot dead as he drove home. Former Prime Minister Raila Odinga on Friday suggested the killing of Jacob Juma on Thursday night was an assassination and blamed it on the security forces.

Suspected al Shabaab militants shot and killed three village elders, including a Muslim cleric, in in Kwale county, south of Kenya's port city Mombasa on suspicion of helping security agencies fight the insurgents, police said on Monday.
column72: No location given except for Kwale County

column63: Five people were killed and 11 wounded on Friday when shells hit a political rally in support of armed forces loyal to the internationally recognised parliament in Tobruk in the centre of Libya's second city Benghazi, a medical source said.

At least six civilians died and another seven were injured in an attack reportedly carried out by Boko Haram jihadists in Niger, the army said on Friday. The attack occurred on Thursday evening in the village of Yebi near the southeastern town of Bosso, close to the Nigerian frontier, authorities confirmed. Medicins sans Frontieres confirmed the attack and casualties.
column67: Deutsche Welle, Radio France Internationale, Paris

column63: Nineteen persons have been killed at Ula-Upata and Edoha in Ahoada East local government area of Rivers State by gunmen suspected to be members of a cult group.

Twenty herdsmen and 83 cows were reportedly killed over the weekend in Adayi and Loko areas of Nasarawa LGA of Nasarawa State by gunmen suspected to be from the riverine areas of Benue and Nasarawa states.

Gunmen on Sunday night killed Bala Madaki, the district head of Fadan Karshi in Numana Chiefdom of Sanga Local Government Area of Kaduna State. Mr. Madaki was killed alongside his nephew, Emmanuel Tanko, 19, at his residence in Fadan Karshi.
In Ejule, Ofu Local government area of Kogi State where a traditional ruler, Simon Shaibu was gunned down and killed. The victim was involved in a dispute over the chieftaincy of the community.

column13: Korum, Orawua and Gidan Bature villages
column63: At least six persons were killed and many others wounded when some unidentified gunmen attacked Korum, Orawua and Gidan Bature villages in Gassol Local Government Area of Taraba State on Sunday.
column67: The Guardian, Premium Times, Daily Trust

column63: The spokesman of Myetti Allah Cattle Breeders Association of Nigeria (MACBAN), Garus Gololo, who said the reason for the Friday night attack on the Tiv people of Agwabi village in Binev Council Ward in Buruku Local Government Area of the state which led to the death of five people was due to the killing of 800 cattle by Tiv youths.

Boko Haram invaded five communities of Ladin Buta near Khaddamari village of Jere Local Government Area of Borno state around 7pm on Tuesday and set ablaze many houses after killing 13 residents and injuring scores of others.
Gunmen suspected to be cultists Saturday night killed eight persons including the oldest man in Ozochi, Ahoada East LGA of Rivers State in an attack whose motive was unclear.

Six persons were killed Sunday night in Ibaa Community, Emohua Local Government Area of Rivers State, by gunmen suspected to be cultists [gangsters] from the Greenlanders gang seeking reprisals against their rivals, the Icelanders.

column36: members of the Movement for the Actualisation of Sovereign State of Biafra (MASSOB)
column63: No fewer than five civilians have been confirmed dead following protest by members of the Movement for the Actualisation of Sovereign State of Biafra (MASSOB), in Asaba on Monday.

During yesterday's rally in Onitsha, Anambra State, a combined team of the military and police clashed with members of Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB) during the celebration of Biafra Day in the commercial city. The clash, THISDAY checks revealed, left 32 people dead and many injured.
Unidentified gunmen in Karachi have killed a Pakistani rights activist known for campaigning against religious extremism, police officials said. Two people were also wounded in the attack.

Unknown gunmen broke into the home of politician Armando Ceballos in Lantapan, a remote town about 840 kilometres (520 miles) south of Manila at dawn Saturday and shot him dead, a provincial police spokesman said.
Seven people were killed while one was wounded in an ambush in Rosario town in Cavite Province early morning Monday [9 May], police said. Police suspect the incident was related to local elections.
column67: Philippine Daily Inquirer website in English 09 May 16
column72: Geonames lists about 100 ""Rosario""s in the Philippines; this location is for ""Rosario Cavite Police Station"" from Google Maps

column63: Six children - three of them from one family - have reportedly been killed in air strikes my MiG fighter jets on residential areas within Heiban town in the Nuba mountains in South Kordofan.
An attack by armed tribesmen near a makeshift camp for displaced people in Sortoni in the North Darfur region killed six civilians, including two children, a resident and a UN official said Tuesday.
column72: Could not geolocate Sortoni camp so location is arbitrary

column63: Eight displaced people were slain, and five others sustained injuries, in attacks by armed Abbala tribesmen at the Azerni refugee camp near El Geneina, including a shooting in a mosque on Sunday evening.
About 10 people were reportedly killed while more than 15 were also wounded in the 18 May fighting in Beledweyne district in Hiiraan region between two clan militias.

Reports received by Raxanreeb Online say that 15 have died of hunger in Beledweyne, the capital Hiiraan Region, over past 24 hours. Seventeen others were killed in the latest [clan] clashes in the town.
column67: Raxanreeb website in Somali 0000 gmt 21 May 16
column72: Just getting fragmentary reports here: presumably if 15 people died of hunger on one day there were many more; also it is unclear whether the 17 are combatants

column63: Turkish authorities have identified the remains of 13 people from two families killed after a truck carrying more than 15 tonnes of explosives blew up last week in Sarikamis outside the city of Diyarbakir in the country's mainly Kurdish southeast, raising the toll in the blast to 16. 23 people were wounded in the explosion. Authorities say the blast was caused by the accidental detonation of explosives the PKK were transporting in a truck.

The leader of a Venezuelan the New Time opposition party (UNT) in the state capital Barquisimeto of the northwestern state of Lara was shot in the head and killed by unidentified attackers, authorities said Friday.
Eleven people, including a Colombian national and three minors, were killed by a group of armed men in the state of Trujillo in Venezuela, the Attorney General's office said Sunday.
column72: No location given except for Trujillo state; no additional details could be found in a web search for other reports of the incident.

column63: Seven people were killed and more than 15 wounded by a bomb on Friday in the Yemeni city Marib, east of the capital Sanaa, police told Reuters.
Yemeni officials: Suicide bombing outside a police base in the southern city of Mukalla kills 12.
column72: That's everything in the story: I'm assuming the ``outside'' means civilians were killed

column63: An air strike by the Saudi-led coalition killed eleven civilians from the same family by mistake on Wednesday, a provincial official said. Emirati warplanes targeted the home of a suspected member of the Islamic State (IS) jihadist group in Huta, the capital of southern Lahij province, but missed and hit an adjacent house, the official told AFP.

column13: Tse Aondo and Tse Ankyou villages
column63: Police spokesman in the state confirmed seven persons killed in the mid-day invasion of the Tiv speaking villages of Tse Aondo and Tse Ankyou in Ukum local government area, although the villagers said over 10 people were killed in both communities which have now been deserted for fear of further invasion.
At least five people were killed on Monday [30 May] as unidentified men opened fire at them in Kech District's Mand area near the Pakistan-Iran border. The motive for the attack was unclear.
column67: Express Tribune website in English 0000 gmt 1 Jun 16

column63: Eight people have been beheaded at Kibatini in Amboni area in Tanga City [northern Tanzania] by unidentified assailants, police confirmed yesterday. The motive for the attack is unclear.
column67: Daily News website, Dar es Salaam

column63: The head of the development council and a government employee have been killed by gunmen on a motorcycle in Ghanikhel District, Nangarhar Province.
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column63: An Afghan member of parliament was killed by a bomb planted near his residence in the capital Kabul on Sunday, the interior ministry said. The Taliban claimed responsibility for the attack. Six civilians were wounded in the attack.
column67: Ariana TV, Kabul, Voice of Jihad website in Pashto 05 Jun 16

column63: At least eight people were killed and 18 injured Monday morning when a motorcycle bomb exploded in a crowded market in Afghanistan's northeastern Badakhshan province, local authorities said.
column72: No geographical details except the province.

column63: Afghan officials say the Taliban have killed at least five people from a group of eight abducted earlier this month from a bus in northern Kunduz province. The five were among eight passengers abducted on a bus in Chardara district on earlier in June.
The head of the appeal court of Rashidan District of Ghazni Province has been killed by unidentified armed men in Kabul city.
column67: Tolo News in Dari 0430 gmt 29 Jun 16

column63: Suspected militants in Bangladesh hacked an elderly Hindu priest to death on Tuesday when he was on his way to the temple he served in Jhenaidah district, about 100 miles (161 km) west of Dhaka

An indigenous activist was shot dead in southwestern Brazil and at least six others seriously wounded when their camp was attacked by armed farmers, a government agency said. The campaigners had set up a camp near the city of Caarapo in a push to have their ancestral land claims to be formally recognised by the government when they were attacked by about 70 farmers riding motorcycles, trucks and a tractor, witnesses said.

column29: Fulanis and members of the former Seleka
column63: At least 10 people died and several others were hurt by armed Fulanis and members of the former Seleka during an attack in the Ngaoundaye region in the northwest
column67: Radio France Internationale in French 1830 gmt 16 Jun 16, Radio Ndeke Luka in Sango 1215 gmt 15 Jun 16
column72: No information on locality, though one report calls Ngaoundaye a ``city'' and the French Wikipedia shows it as a small (pop. 4000) border town

column63: Boko Haram militants killed 10 fishermen in Touboun Ali in Cameroon near the Nigerian border on 6 June.
column72: Could not geolocate Touboun Ali ; coordinates are for arbitrary location near lake and Nigerian border

column63: The bodies of 42 fishermen, who were killed by the Islamist group, Boko Haram, have been pulled from Lake Chad in Cameroon, the country's military has announced. The men had been seized on 8 June from the village of Darak, located near the Nigerian border.
column72: Location approximate: article mentioned attack near Nigerian border

column63: At least 11 people have been killed and four injured in a suicide bombing by a Boko Haram jihadist in Djakana in the commune of Mora, Mayo-Sava in northern Cameroon, a security source said Thursday.
column72: .Could not geolocate Djakana; coordinates are for Mayo-Sava

column63: The Egyptian branch of the Islamic State group claimed responsibility for a shooting attack that killed a Coptic priest in the North Sinai capital of El-Arish on Thursday.

A lawmaker who campaigned for Britain to stay in the European Union was killed Thursday by a gun- and knife-wielding attacker in her small-town constituency. Jo Cox, a 41-year-old Labour Party legislator who praised the contribution of immigrants to Britain and championed the cause of war-scarred Syrian refugees, was attacked outside a library in Birstall, northern England, after a regular meeting with constituents.
column72: Hundreds of additional articles

column63: A television journalist walking with his grandson in a city streetin Chiquimula in eastern Guatemala was shot dead by two assailants on a motorbike Tuesday.

A leader in Honduras' gay community has been buried several days after he was kidnapped and killed in the city of San Pedro Sula. Rene Martinez, 39, was a city employee working in anti-violence outreach programs and a rising member of the National Party.

The mayor of Reitoca in Honduras is believed to lead a gang which killed five people on Sunday. On that day, unidentified gunmen fired on a vehicle carrying members of a local church, killing one of the occupants and wounding another. When other people tried to transfer the body and the wounded person to hospital, another attack was mounted that killed four people.

At least 22 people were killed when police clashed with squatters in Mathura, in Uttar Pradesh in north India, officials said on Friday, the violence erupting after protesters killed two police officers during an operation to clear thousands of people from a public park. More than 100 people were injured in the melee.
A suicide bombing against a military checkpoint in Tarmiyah, about 30 miles (50 kilometers) north of the capital, killed five civilians and wounded 15 others.
Three separate car bomb attacks on markets and a restaurant in Baghdad killed seven people.
The governor of Anbar province said said 49 Sunni men in Fallujah had been executed after surrendering to a Shi'ite militia group.
column72: Governor gave dates as between 3 and 5 June; an additional 643 men are missing.

column63: A number of families attempted to escape from ISIS organisation by crossing Euphrates from Al-Na'imiya area to Amiriyat al-Fallujah, 19 km south of Fallujah. When the two boats reached the middle of the river, ISIS elements shot at them, which led the boats to sink and 13 people, most of them children, drowned
A car bomb in Iraq's Shiite holy city of Karbala killed 10 civilians and wounded 26 others on Tuesday, officials said.

A suicide car bomb attack took place in a commercial area of a majority Shiite neighborhood in Baghdad. At least 19 civilians were killed and 46 wounded, police said. ISIS has claimed responsibility for the attack.

suicide bomber rammed his explosives-laden car into an Iraqi army checkpoint north of Baghdad, killing at least seven civilians in the town of Taji, about 20 kilometers (12 miles) north of the capital, a police officer said. At least 32 people were wounded. In an online statement, the Islamic State group claimed responsibility for the attack.
Fighters from the Islamic State group killed at least 18 members of two families and wounded at least 17 as they attempted to flee the besieged jihadist bastion of Fallujah, relatives said on Sunday.

At least 12 people were killed and 32 wounded early on Tuesday when a suicide bomber wearing a vest packed with explosives attacked a Sunni mosque in Abu Ghraib, about 25 km (15 miles) west of the Iraqi capital, police and medics said.
Four suicide bombers killed at least six people and wounded 19 more in a series of attacks in the Lebanese Christian village of Qaa at the border with Syria on Monday, security sources said.
At least seven civilians have been killed and eight wounded by shelling in the past two days in the eastern Libyan city of Benghazi, a hospital official said on Saturday.
Gunmen have killed 12 Libyans a day after their release from jail for taking part in acts of repression during the 2011 revolt against Moamer Kadhafi, officials said on Sunday.
A suicide car bomber hit a checkpoint at a Libyan police station west of the besieged Islamic State stronghold of Sirte on Thursday, killing 10 people and wounding seven, officials said.
column72: Casualties probably include some combatants but article explicitly says there were civilians killed

column63: A car bomb has gone off outside a hospital in the eastern Libyan city of Benghazi, killing five people and wounding 14, security and hospital officials said.

Gunmen marched into the remote mountain village El Mirador, a community in central Puebla state, near Oaxaca in Mexico on Friday and killed 11 members of the same family, including two children, authorities said. An official at the prosecutor's office said authorities are trying to establish whether the crime was related to organized crime or a family dispute: the village was evangelical and had split from a nearby Catholic village.
column72: Geonames shows two ``El Mirador'' villages in Puebla; coordinates are for one of those.

column63: Seven people, including a local journalist, were killed when teacher protests turned violent near the town of Asuncion Nochixtlan in the Mexican state of Oaxaca, authorities said. The clashes between teachers, state police and local residents also left 53 civilians injured, according to the Oaxaca state government.

14 people were killed and 46 injured in clashes over land between residents of two central Malian villages, a regional official told AFP Sunday. The clash pitted villagers from Koussouma and Mougna near the ancient town of Djenne on Saturday, with both sides claiming ownership over arable land nearby, the official from the province of Mopti said on condition of anonymity.
column67: ORTM TV in French 2045 gmt 27 Jun 16
column72: Been there: it's endless mudflats in the rainy season. Can't they all just get along??

column63: In Aluu community, Ikwerre Local Government Areas of Rivers State, on Saturday, gunmen suspected to be members of a cult group allegedly gunned down 23 persons, including a nursing mother.

Some gunmen, suspected to be members of a cult [gang] group, in the early hours of yesterday, killed 11 persons in Emohua Local Government Area of Rivers State in a fresh cult clash. The cultists visited their activities on three communities in the area, Rumuji, Ovogo and Rumuewhuo.
Gunmen on Monday evening killed the youth leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC) identified as Sunny Omokaro, in Ward 4 in Ikpoba-Okha local government area of Edo State.
Gunmen suspected to be members of a cult group early on Wednesday, killed seven students of the Federal University of Agriculture Makurdi (UAM) as they attacked a students' hostel
column67: Daily Trust, Leadership, The Sun website, Lagos

column63: Twenty-four people were killed when Boko Haram fighters opened fire on mourners near the town of Gulak in Adamawa state, northeast Nigeria, a local community leader told AFP on Friday. 10 persons sustained various degrees of injuries from the attack.
column67: The Guardian website in English 1905 gmt 17 Jun 16, This Day, The Guardian

column63: No fewer than 11 persons were killed on Wednesday in Omoku, the headquarters of Ogba/Egbema/Ndoni Local Government Area (ONELGA) of Rivers State by suspected cultists.

column13: Turan, Uzaar, Anyii and Vase villages
column63: In what seemed like a coordinated attacks, suspected Fulani herdsmen yesterday allegedly attacked four Benue communities in Logo and Ukum LGAs killing over 26 persons, injuring many others and razing several houses and huts.
No fewer than eight persons are feared to have been killed and several injured in renewed clashes between the Ochienyim and Adadama communities in Cross River and Ebonyi States.
At least eight persons have died and seven were injured in a clash between Fulani herdsmen and farmers in Koh community in Girei Local Government Area of Adamawa State.

Six people have been killed in the Igbo-Olomu and Ishawo villages in the Ikorodu district on the outskirts of Lagos, police and the state government said on Sunday, blaming "suspected militants", said to be oil thieves from the Niger Delta.

One of the most prominent Pakistani singers of Sufi devotional songs, Amjad Sabri, was killed by gunmen who fired into his car in Karachi on Wednesday, and a relative was wounded. A faction of the Pakistani Taliban claimed responsibility, accusing Mr. Sabri of being a blasphemer, but officials said they were investigating the authenticity of the claim.

Somali authorites say security forces have brought to an end a bomb and gun attack by al-Shabab fighters on a central Mogadishu hotel that killed at least 16 people and wounded 55 more. Two legislators were among the dead in Wednesday's attack on Hotel Ambassador. Al-Shabab, the armed Somali group, claimed responsibility for the attack.
column65: AFP, Reuters, AP, BBC, All Africa
column67: Dhacdo.com website, Hargeysa, Radio Shabeelle, Mogadishu, Al Jazeera

column63: Unidentified gunmen have shot dead a female journalist working for the state-run radio and television on Sunday afternoon in the Somali capital, police said.
column67: Shabelle Media Network website, Mogadishu, Hiiraan in Somali 5 Jun 16, Hiiraan in Somali on 5 Jun 16, Dalsan Radio, Liberian Observer

column63: Aerial bombardments during the past week struck areas of western Jebel Marra east of Nierteti and killed six villagers in total, as well as wounding 18. Dozens of homes were burnt and a number of livestock was killed.
column72: Could not geolocate Nierteti; coordinates are for arbitrary location in western Jebel Marra. Article also somewhat unclear on the exact date but named the victims.

column63: Armed gunmen have on Wednesday morning shot and killed Darkeynley deputy district commissioner. Armed group Al-Shabaab have claimed the responsibility for the killing of Abdullahi Ibrahim Isbiimo who was also director of monitoring and evaluations at Banadir administration.
column72: Could not geolocate Darkeynley; coordinates are for Banadir district

column63: Seven people were killed, including the Imam of a mosque, and six others were wounded on Wednesday in an attack by Abbala herdsmen on farmers in Um Tajok, Kereinik locality in West Darfur.

At least 12 people have been killed, including the state minister of environment, and 20 others wounded when armed militants from Al Shabaab stormed Nasa-Hablod, a popular hotel in the heart of Somalia's seashore capital, Mogadishu on Saturday. Al Shabaab has claimed credit for the hotel attack.
column65: Reuters, AFP, CNN, AP, NYT, All Africa

column63: Unidentified pistol-wielding men have shot and killed a local council member in northern Galkayo town, the headquarters of Mudug province in central Somalia, a witness said on Monday.

Somali officials say at least 20 people have been killed in a massive roadside explosion that engulfed a passenger bus at Lafole town on the main highway linking Mogadishu to Afgoye, 30 kilometers west of the capital.

Eight displaced Syrians, including four children, were killed by Turkish border guards while trying to flee their war-torn country Sunday morning, the Syrian Observatory for Human Rights said. Eight more people were wounded.
column72: Location approximate: article the victims were fleeing the town of Manbij. Also not clear which side of border, so technically this might have been in Syria (the incident is not in the other Syrian data)

column63: Clashes between the Sudan People's Liberation Army (SPLA) and members of the Fertit tribe began on June 24, say sources in the city. The SPLA is predominantly made up of members of the Dinka tribe. At least 43 people were killed in the fighting, according to a government statement on June 28.
column72: Total may include some combatants, but eyewitness reports, including several from UN personnel, indicate there were substantial civilian casualties

column63: Forty-four people were killed and 239 others were wounded in a suicide bomb attack at Istanbul's main international airport on Tuesday
column65: AP, CNN, AFP, Reuters, All Africa
column72: Hundreds of additional articles

column63: At least 17 civilians ‚Äî including 10 women and one girl ‚Äî were killed and at least 122 were wounded when rockets hit a busy market in the western city of Taiz on Friday, Yemeni and MSF medical officials said. The rockets were fired by Houthi rebels who are besieging the city.

An airstrike early on Tuesday by a Saudi-led coalition targeting a truck transporting weapons for Shiite rebels in Yemen's southern province of Taiz killed 19 civilians and wounded 8, security officials said.
column72: Location approximate: articles mention Taiz province (not city) but gives no other detail beyond ``a commercial road that lies between two villages''

column63: In Taiz, 11 civilians and a soldier were killed when rebels bombed a residential area, a military official said.
At least seven civilians, including two children, were killed in two air raids Tuesday that hit a Yemeni town, Mahfid, controlled by Al-Qaeda, a local official and tribesmen said.
A Saudi-led coalition air strike killed 10 Yemeni civilians and wounded at least another 15 in a village market for smuggled fuel in the Hayfan district in the southern province of Lahj on Tuesday
column72: Geonames puts Hayfan in Taiz, not Lahj (next province south of Taiz)

column63: Tse Gabo village, in the Nenzev council ward, was attacked by suspected Fulani herdsmen and six persons were killed.

Myanmar soldiers killed at least five civilians in their custody last month in Mong Yaw village and will be prosecuted, a senior general announced Wednesday in a rare case of the military taking responsibility for carrying out atrocities against ethnic minorities.

Boko Haram killed five traders travelling from Gamboru, on the border with Cameroon, to the city of Maiduguri in an ambush on the highway in northeast Nigeria that was recently reopened after coming under repeated attack from the Islamist group, a military source said Wednesday. Three immigration officials were wounded in the attack.
column72: Coordinates for arbitrary location on highway near prior BH activities

column63: About 13 inmates in Abakaliki Prisons in Ebonyi State and one prison guard were believed to have been killed in the early hours of yesterday, when the inmates of the prison rioted over the poor meals served to them by the prison and attempted to escape from the facility. During the riot, the inmates allegedly snatched a rifle from one of the guards in the prison yard and shot some at them, prompting the officials to defend themselves. At least 10 people were injured.
column67: This Day, Rhythm FM in English 0600 gmt 19 Aug 16, Premium Times

column63: A Boko Haram attack on Kuburvwa village which is located between Chibok and Damboa towns of Borno State has left at least 11 people dead.

column63: A Muslim mob in the town of Talata Mafara in northern Nigeria has killed eight people while torching the house of a Muslim man who helped save a Christian student accused of blasphemy, police said Tuesday.
column72: Reports dispute whether the victims were actually Christian or merely thought to be Christian. Student--there is some dispute as to whether he was Christian as well--was rescued by authorities

column63: Hours after a prominent lawyer was gunned down in Pakistan, at least 74 people were killed in a bombing at the hospital where his body was taken. The explosion at a hospital in Quetta on Monday also injured 112 others. Many of those killed in the blast were believed to be lawyers and journalists who had gathered at the hospital to mourn and report on the death of lawyer Bilal Kasi, who had been gunned down earlier in the day. The Islamic State and Jamaatul Ahrar, a splinter group of Tehreek-i-Taliban Pakistan (TTP), both claimed responsibility for the bombing.

column63: A blast from a suspected grenade and gunshots rocked in the Paranaque City jail in metropolitan Manila, leaving 10 inmates dead, including two alleged Chinese drug criminals, officials said Friday. Local government official has been shot and killed by men armed with pistols in Somalia's capital Mogadishu, a witness said.

column63: At least seven civilians were killed on Wednesday in two separate bomb attacks blamed on Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) militants in Turkey's southeast, a regional security source said. Four were killed in a car bomb attack in the centre of the city of Diyarbakir while another three civilians lost their lives in a near simultaneous bombing in Kiziltepe in Mardin province to the south. Both bomb attacks had been aimed at passing police vehicles. At least 38 people are wounded in the two attacks.
column72: Coordinates are for

column63: A suicide bomber aged between 12 and 14 carried out the attack on a wedding party in the Turkish city of Gaziantep on Saturday that killed at least 51 people. An additional 69 people are in hospital and 17 are ""heavily injured"".

The public prosecutor's office said Thursday that it appears somebody threw grenades devices into the Alayon detention center in the town of Maracay, two hours west of Caracas. Two of the devices exploded; 7 prisoners were killed and 47 injured
A Saudi-led coalition air strike killed nine civilians Odhar village in the Nehm area east of the Yemeni capital Sanaa on Sunday night, residents said. An additional 17 people were wounded.

column63: Airstrikes by the Saudi-led coalition bombed a food factory in the Yemeni capital of Sanaa early on Tuesday, killing 14 civilians working on an overnight shift and wounding 10, according to a factory official and medics.

Saudi-led air strikes on a school in a rebel-held province of northern Yemen have killed 10 children and wounded 28 others, Doctors Without Borders (MSF) said on Sunday. "We received 10 dead children and 28 wounded, all under the age of 15, who are victims of air strikes on a Koranic school in Haydan," in Saada province, said MSF spokeswoman Malak Shaher, adding the attack took place on Saturday.

A Saudi-led coalition air strike hit a hospital operated by Medecins Sans Frontieres in the Abs district of Hajja province in northern Yemen on Monday, killing at least 11 people and wounding 19, the aid group said.

An airstrike on a residential area near the Yemeni capital of Sana on Tuesday killed 17 civilians, most of them women and children. The attack on Tuesday took place in the village of Al Madeed in Nehm District, northeast of the capital.
column72: Could not geolocate Al Madeed; coordinates are for Nehm district.

column65: AFP, Reuters, CNN, BBC, All Africa, AP
column67: Radio Okapi website, Kinshasa, Al Jazeera, UN report

column63: A Congo military official and a local leader say Ugandan rebel group the Allied Democratic Forces has attacked a village in the Kasinga-Munzambayi locality about 5 kilometers (3 miles) from Beni in Congo's northeast, killing at least 7 people.

Six civilians have been killed and at least 29 students wounded during fighting between government and militia combatants attributed to traditional chief Kamwena Nsapu in Kananga city, Kasai central province

Land-rights activist Nestor Ivan Martinez was shot dead Sunday in the northern department of Cesar, the fifth rural community leader killed as the government seeks to end a 52-year-old conflict with the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC).
column72: No location given except Cesar Department (province)

column63: Cecilia Coicue, the owner of land where FARC rebels will remain during the process of giving up their weapons, has been murdered on her farm near the hamlet of Corinto in Cauca province, centre-right daily El Espectador reported on 8 September.
Egyptian officials say Islamic State militants have killed five Egyptian civilians they accused of being collaborators and dumped their bodies near the town of Sheikh Zuweid in the Sinai Peninsula.

An Ethiopian human rights group has said that 67 people were killed when fire broke out at a prison housing political prisoners at Addis Ababa's high security Qilinto prison; 22 of the victims died in the fire while the remaining 45 were killed by prison wardens while allegedly trying to escape..  Earlier government reports gave the total as 23.

India on Tuesday killed at least eight people trying to sneak across its disputed border with Pakistan in Kashmir near the town of Uri, army officials said, two days after a deadly assault on an Indian army base that New Delhi blamed on its neighbour.
column72: No indication of the civil/military status of the ""intruders"" and article is inconsistent on whether they are actually killed or just fired on

column63: A series of attacks across Baghdad, including an explosion at a weapons warehouse that set off munitions and sent a huge plume of smoke over the Iraqi capital, killed 15 people and wounded over 50 on Friday, according to Iraqi police and medical officials.

Two suicide attacks have killed six people and injured nine others in the northern Iraqi town of Tuz Khurmato, in Salahuddin province, private Al-Mada Press website reported on 3 September quoting a security source.

ISIS claimed credit for a suicide car bomb attack that killed 12 people and wounded at least 28 others in a market in the Karrada neighborhood central Baghdad on Monday, according to security officials.
column67: Al-Mada website, Baghdad, Telegram messaging service in Arabic 2326 gmt 5 Sep 16

column63: Twelve people were killed and more than 40 wounded late on Friday in two suicide bombings claimed by Islamic State at a shopping mall in eastern Baghdad, police and hospital sources said.
Five explosions in and around Baghdad killed at least 12 people on Saturday and wounded 27 others, police and medical sources said.
Militants killed 12 people and wounded 23 in a shooting and a suicide bombing on Saturday in the northern city of Tikrit

A suicide bomber blew himself up near a small group of Shia pilgrims in a commercial street of Baghdad on Sunday, killing seven people and wounding 28, according to police sources. ISIS has claimed responsibility for the attack.
column67: Telegram messaging service in Arabic 1100 gmt 25 Sep 16

column63: Separate suicide bombings ripped through busy commercial areas in Shiite-dominated neighborhoods of the Iraqi capital on Tuesday, killing at least 17 civilians and wounding 49 others, officials said. In online statements, the Islamic State group claimed responsibility for the attacks.

A gunman on Sunday killed prominent Jordanian writer Nahed Hattar outside a court in Amman where he was facing charges for sharing a cartoon deemed offensive to Islam, state news agency Petra reported.
At least nine civilians including women and children were killed in an air strike near the oasis town of Houn (Hun) in central Libya on Tuesday, a hospital doctor and local officials said.
A journalist in the central Mexican state of Puebla was killed in a highway shooting near the community of Huauchinango, authorities said Thursday.
Two priests were found dead in eastern Mexico on Monday hours after they were kidnapped from their church in Poza Rica, Veracruz.

A Mexican priest was found murdered in the central state of Michoacan five days after being abducted from his parish residence in the rural town of Janamuato, the state attorney general said on Sunday,
A provincial lawmaker from Mozambique's opposition movement has been killed by gunmen while walking to his house in Moatize town in Tete province on Thursday.
Five people, four young Niger nationals and a foreigner, were on Friday night killed in the village of Toumour, in the region of Diffa. Two more villagers were wounded.
column72: Some victims might have been part of the local self-defense force; accounts are ambiguous on this.

column63: At least eight people were killed outside a church in the village of Kwamjilari, Borno state in a suspected Boko Haram attack carried out by gunmen on bicycles in northeast Nigeria, local residents said on Monday.

Suspected members of the Islamist militant group Boko Haram killed six civilians in an attack on a commercial convoy being escorted by the army on the road from Damboa to Maiduguri in Nigeria's northeastern state of Borno, the military said on Monday.
column72: Coordinates for arbitrary location on highway between Damboa and Maiduguri

column63: The traditional ruler of Mbayongo district in Katsina Ala local council of Benue State, Tyoor Awuha Alev, has been killed by unknown gunmen. He was shot dead at his palace in Vingir village around 8:00p.m. on Sunday.

In Okposi and Obaji communities of Ogba/Egbema/Ndoni Local Government Area (ONELGA), six persons reportedly died following a supremacy battle between members of two rival cult groups, Greenlanders and Icelanders.

The residents of Igbogbo community of Ikorodu, Lagos State were in the early hours of yesterday thrown into mourning as gunmen shot and killed all six members of a family, including a three-month-old baby and a three-year-old child.
column72: No indication of motive, though local sources do not think it was a robbery

column63: At least 14 people were killed and more than 50 wounded after a suicide bomber attacked a court in the Pakistani city of Mardan Friday, police said. Pakistani Taliban faction Jamaat-ur-Ahrar on Friday claimed responsibility for the attack.

Pakistani police say gunmen have killed a physician who was instrumental in an anti-polio drive in the northwestern city of Peshawar. A faction of the Pakistani Taliban, Jamaat-ul-Ahrar, on Sunday claimed responsibility for the attack.

A suicide attack at a Sunni mosque in Pai Khan, a remote village in the mountainous Ambar subdistrict of Mohmand killed at least 36 people Friday, an official told CNN. Local administrator Mohammad Younus of Baluchistan's Panjgur district said gunmen killed six people from the same family in an isolated house.

At least six people were killed and 35 wounded on Monday, when an improvised explosive device tore into a crowded marketplace in Darzab district of the province of Jawzja in a northern Afghan province on the border with Turkmenistan, officials said.
A gunman opened fire in a Shiite shrine in Kabul on Tuesday morning, killing 18 civilians and wounding at least 50 before Afghan security forces killed him
A bomb blast outside a Shiite mosque in Balkh District of northern Balkh Province in Afghanistan on Wednesday killed at least 14 people and wounded 24 among a gathering of worshippers

The U.N. peacekeeping mission in Central African Republic says 11 people were killed and 14 injured in violence in Bangui's PK5 neighborhood this week sparked by the killing of a military official.

Fighters from Central African Republic's largely Muslim 'Seleka' militia attacked refugees in Ngakobo near the town of Kaga Bandoro in the country's remote north on Wednesday, stabbing or hacking to death at least 11 people and wounded 10 before U.N. peacekeepers dispersed them, witnesses said.
