At least 16 people were killed and 46 wounded in an explosion and two suicide bombings in Baghdad on Monday [3 October], security officials said.

Iraqi officials say three bomb attacks have killed 10 people and wounded at least 37 across the Iraqi capital, largely in Shiite areas. In a statement, the Islamic State group claims responsibility for the largest attack
At least six civilians were killed by a suicide bomber in a car that targeted a checkpoint in Adhaim in northern Iraq on Sunday, police and medical sources said.

Islamic State group (IS) has claimed responsibility for a suicide bombing that it said targeted on 10 October Shia pilgrims at an army checkpoint at the entrance of the town of Khalis, north of Baghdad where at least nine people were killed and 11 wounded.

column63: ISIS has 24 former Iraq Security Forces officers in Mosul, according to UN rights office reports.
ISIS has slaughtered 190 ex-Iraq Security Forces officers in Mosul, according to UN rights office reports.
42 civilians were reportedly shot in the head in the Hamam al-Alil district outside Mosul, a UN rights office statement said, apparently for refusing to follow the IS group's instructions.
Seven people have been killed and 10 others injured in a suicide attack on a Shia rally in Baghdad.
More than 20 people were put to death by ISIS as punishment for a revolt in two villages, Al-Hudd and Al-Lazzaga, located just north of the town of Qayyara

Iraqi police say a parked car bomb has exploded in Baghdad's northwestern neighborhood of Hurriyah, killing at least 10 and wounding 34. The bombing, which hit a popular fruit and vegetable market in a commercial street of the predominantly Shiite neighborhood, was the fifth such explosion in the capital on Sunday. The day's casualty toll from the attacks in Baghdad now stands at 17 dead and over 60 wounded.

Gunmen from al-Shabab killed six people in an attack in a residential block near Bulla Public Works in Mandera near the border with Somalia, an official said Thursday. The group claimed, through its Andulus radio station, it had targeted Christians.
The Somali Islamist group al Shabaab said it had carried out an attack on Thursday near Mandera in northeast Kenya, near the border with Somalia, in which six Christians were killed.

column63: A bomb blast at a guesthouse in Mandera in northeast Kenya killed at least 12 people on Tuesday, in an attack claimed by Shabaab militants which last hit the area earlier this month.

column63: Islamic extremist gunmen from neighboring Somalia killed 12 people in an attack on non-Muslims in Kenya's northern Mandera County, an official said Tuesday. Somalia's al-Shabab rebels claimed responsibility for the early-morning attack on the Bishaaro Guest House in Mandera, saying its fighters targeted Christians, according to the group's Andalus radio station.

On Friday, the bodies of 10 unidentified men were found in a dumpster in Benghazi. The bodies bore torture marks and had gunshot wounds to the head, according to a statement by the Support and Reinforcement security unit which found them.
A car exploded in the eastern city of Benghazi late Saturday, killing four people including a prominent anti-corruption activist, officials said. At least 23 people were wounded in the attack.
column72: One report says car bomb, the other a mortar shell that hit a group of cars. So possibly not an assassination

column72: Could not geolocate Myothugyi village; coordinates are for Maungdaw township

column63: According to the UN human rights office, six people were hanged by ISIS in Mosul on Oct. 20 for hiding SIM cards

column39: 40 former members of the Iraqi Security Forces
column63: Islamic State militants killed 40 former members of the Iraqi Security Forces near Mosul on Saturday and threw their bodies in the Tigris river, U.N. human rights spokeswoman Ravina Shamdasani said on Tuesday

column36: Renamo's chief in the provincial assembly in Sofala
column63: Juma Ramos, Renamo's chief in the provincial assembly in Sofala was shot and killed by two unidentified gunmen in Beira, Mozambique
Pakistan's Foreign Ministry said in a statement that six civilians on the Pakistani side in the Nikial and Jandrot areas had been killed by shelling from India Monday, and eight injured.
column72: Coordinates are for Nikial

column63: Venezuelan lawmakers voted unanimously Tuesday to issue a declaration condemning the massacre of 12 civilians by soldiers in the town of Barlovento. The victims were abducted on 16 Oct and their rotting bodies were recently discovered in a mass grave. According to an opposition legislator, an additional 14 people are still missing. The soldiers involved have been arrested are being charged with murder.
column72: Exact date of death is uncertain, but probably proximate to date of abduction.

column63: An Afghan official says a roadside bombing has killed seven civilians in Sayedkhail district, Parwan province.
column72: Could not geolocate Sayedkhail; coordinates are for Khail

column63: A roadside explosion killed 11 people and wounded 12 others on Thursday when they struck a roadside bomb in Kosa Qala village in Faryab province

At least 32 people were killed and more than 50 wounded when a suicide bomber struck a crowded gathering of Shiite Muslims in the Afghan capital on Monday, officials said. The Islamic State issued a statement by its central Amaq news agency saying that the group‚Äôs affiliates in Afghanistan had been responsible for the assault.
column65: AP, AFP, BBC, CNN, Reuters, NYT
column67: Tolo News in Dari 0900 gmt 21 Nov 16, Tolo News, Kabul

column72: Casualty figures from UN; government says 27 dead and 35 wounded

column63: Members of the Amazon rainforest indigenous Yanomami tribe have shot dead six illegal gold miners with arrows in the Amazonian state of Roraima on the frontier with Venezuela, Brazilian officials said Friday.
column72: Coordinates for arbitrary location in Roraima near Venezuela. Date was only reported as ""early in the month"" so it is approximate.

column28: Popular Front for the Renaissance of Central African Republic (FPRC) fighters
column63: Human Rights Watch puts the civilian death total from an incident where Popular Front for the Renaissance of Central African Republic (FPRC) fighters in Central African Republic hunted down and massacred members of the Fulani ethnic group during violence at 14 civilians, with another 76 wounded. The incident occurred this week in Bria, a town about 600 km (370 miles) northeast of the capital Bangui
column72: Earlier UN report said 85 were killed but this was probably confusing total casualties (HRW keeps the 76 wounded figure) with those killed.

column63: A Congolese press freedom group says a state television reporter was killed in his home in the central town of Mbuji-Mayi by unidentified assailants.

An ethnic Nande Mai Mai Mazembe militia in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo killed 37 civilians, mostly Hutus, on Sunday morning the village of Luhanga in Lubero territory in North Kivu province, local sources said
column67: Radio Okapi (Goma) in French 1900 gmt 27 Nov 16
column72: Could not geolocate Luhanga village; coordinates are for Lubero

column63: At least seven civilians on the Indian side of the Line of Control (LoC) in the Ramgrah sector of India's Samba district and Manjakote area of Rajouri district were killed Tuesday and 15 others injured in shelling that came from the Pakistani side, according to local Indian authorities.
column72: Coordinates are for Samba district

column63: Two roadside bombs struck a convoy carrying Iraqi families fleeing an Islamic State-controlled town of Hawija as the victims were passing in Al-Alam neighbourhood near Tikrit, killing 17 civilians, a police officer said

A suicide attacker detonated an ambulance packed with explosives in Tikrit on Sunday, killing six civilians and wounding at least 25 at the southern entrance to the city, police and hospital sources said. ISIS claimed responsibility for the attack.
column67: Amaq news agency in Arabic 1045 gmt 6 Nov 16, Telegram messaging service in Arabic 6 Nov 16, Tasnim news agency website, Tehran

column63: In the city of Samarra a suicide attacker set off a bomb-packed ambulance in a parking lot near Shiite pilgrims before detonating his explosives vest. The attack killed 11 people, including at least four Iranians, and wounded up to 100 other people. ISIS has claimed responsibility for the attack.
column67: Amaq news agency in Arabic 1045 gmt 6 Nov 16, Telegram messaging service in Arabic 6 Nov 16, Tasnim news agency website, Tehran

column63: 40 civilians were reportedly shot on Tuesday for "treason and collaboration" with Iraqi government forces, and their bodies hung from electrical poles around Mosul, the U.N. human rights office said on Friday.
According to the U.N. human rights office, ISIS Wednesday reportedly shot to death 20 civilians in the Ghabat Military Base near Mosul on charges of leaking information.

The UN human rights office reported that on Nov. 11, ISIL reportedly shot and killed 12 civilians in Bakir neighborhood of eastern Mosul city for allegedly refusing to let it install rockets on the rooftops of their houses.

The attack in Ain al-Tamer, which involved six suicide bombers, some of whom may have been killed by security forces before they blew themselves up, killed eight people and wounded at least six, the officials said. ISIS claimed responsibility for the attack.
column72: Some reports say 6 killed

column63: Eight people were killed and about 25 wounded when two suicide bombers blew up their cars at police checkpoints in Falluja. ISIS claimed responsibility for the attack

A suicide car bomb targeted a wedding party in Amriyat al-Fallujah, Iraq, killing 20 people and wounding 40 others, according to the head of the town council. ISIS, in a Twitter post, claimed responsibility for the bombing
Three explosive devices have reportedly exploded in three areas in the Iraqi capital Baghdad, leaving five people killed and 19 others injured
Five people have reportedly been killed and 15 others injured in two bombings in Baghdad on 20 November.

A suicide truck bomb killed 92 people, most of them Iranian Shi'ite pilgrims, at a petrol station in the city of Hilla 100 km (62 miles) south of Baghdad on Thursday, police and medical sources said. 105 people were wounded in the attack. The Islamic State claimed responsibility for the attack in an online statement.
column65: BBC, AP, AFP, CNN, NYT, Reuters
column67: Al-Mada website, Baghdad, Press TV, Tehran, Al-Arabiya TV, Dubai

column63: Information received by the U.N. showed that ISIS militants publicly shot to death 27 civilians in Muhandiseen Park in northern Mosul on Nov. 25
A medical source in Iraq's northern city of Mosul said that 16 civilians had been killed in mortar shelling and random shooting by the Islamic State (IS) militant group in the city.

column29: Awled Suleiman tribe and Guedadfa tribe
column63: Activists and medics say clashes between Awled Suleiman tribal members and the Guedadfa tribe that erupted in Sebha in southern Libya after three young men turned a pet monkey loose on a high school girl have killed at least 20 people and wounded 50. Witnesses said several homes were hit by rockets and shells in the confrontation.
Libya's top religious authority, Dar al-Ifta, said Monday that one of its most senior members had been killed, more than a month after he was kidnapped in Tripoli.

column12: between the towns of Tixtla and Atliaca
column63: "The bodies of nine males with visible signs of torture" were discovered on Sunday night on a road between the towns of Tixtla and Atliaca, in Guerrero's central region, the state's secretary of security said in a statement.

Eighteen people -- mostly women, children and the elderly -- were killed and 43 others were wounded on Tuesday in violence near the village of Bangui in Niger when farmers armed with knives attacked a settlement of cattle herders, officials said. The attacks occurred Tuesday morning after a herd of cattle wandered into a farmer's field and damaged cereal crops.

At least nine persons were killed on Tuesday morning when improvised explosive devices conveyed in a pickup van exploded near a military checkpoint along Gubio road in Maiduguri, killing all passengers on board.
column72: No details as to whether this was a planned attack by all passangers or a bomber among the passengers

column63: Not less than five people have been killed, and several injured, as cattle rustlers went on rampage in Gbada community in Kaure village in Shiroro local government area of Niger state.
Gunmen numbering three on Wednesday killed a community leader, Pa Osarobo Ajayi, in Okha village, Ovia South West local government area of Edo State.

At least 40 illegal gold miners have been shot dead by suspected armed cattle rustlers at a mining site in Gidan Ardo Village of Bindin district in Maru local government area of Zamfara state. Many other people were wounded.

column13: Ungwan Rimi, Kitakum, Ungwan Magaji and Kigam villages
column63: 31 people were reportedly killed by suspected Fulani herdsmen in attacks in four villages in Chawai Chiefdom of Kamaru Ward in Kauru local government of Kaduna State.

Eight civilians were killed and at least seven wounded yesterday when security agents and members of the Islamic Movement in Nigeria (IMN), otherwise known as Shi'ites clashed in Kano City over the yearly procession of the group.
At least 22 persons were killed in two days of attacks this week by suspected Boko Haram gunmen in Monguno Local Government Area of Borno State, security sources said.
Six persons were killed, and several women and children injured, in an attack by suspected cattle rustlers in Kukoki community, Shiroro Local Government Area of Niger State.
Six prisoners were confirmed dead and 11 injured after officials responded to a disturbance at Oke Kura Prison, Ilorin City, Kwara State
column72: Guards are accused of beating prisoners to death; officials deny this but confirmed the death total.

column13: Dole, Tudun Bugaje and Kwangwami communities
column63: At least 25 people were killed on Saturday night when gunmen stormed Dole, Tudun Bugaje and Kwangwami communities in Zurmi Local Government Area in Zamfara State .
column67: Premium Times, This Day, Daily Trust

column63: An explosion claimed by militant group Islamic State ripped through a Sufi shrine in the remote Khuzdar district of Pakistan's Baluchistan province on Saturday, killing at least 52 people and wounding 105, officials said.
column67: Telegram messaging service in Arabic 1726 gmt 12 Nov 16

column63: A Philippine mayor who had been accused of drug trafficking by President Rodrigo Duterte was shot and killed by police officers in his jail cell in Leyte's Baybay city on Saturday, the police said; his cell-mate was also killed.
column72: Police claim victim was killed during a "firefight" that occurred while they were searching his cell for drugs. Others, including a member of the Philippine Commission on Human Rights and a later 6-Dec-2016 report by the National Bureau of Investigation, are skeptical of this account.

column63: Armed herders have shot and killed a South Darfur sheikh as he tried to protect his farm in the Nbakaah area of Gereida locality from their livestock on Wednesday.
column72: Could not geolocate Nbakaah; coordinates are for Gereida. Not clear if this was political: ""sheikh"" can be a fairly low-level honorific

column63: Seven people were killed, three others were wounded, and about ten villages have been burnt in the Gireida area in attacks by armed herders: the burned villages include Dendora, Matiya, Haraza, Dahab Sharro, Mayol, Kafla and Rowena.
Somali security forces have detained two suspects whom they said have shot and killed a traditional elder in Mogadishu's Wadajir district on Wednesday afternoon, an official said Wednesday.

A member of Somali parliament said Al shabaab fighters have beheaded five men in Tiyeglow for allegedly collaborating with retreating allied forces, days after they took the town from Somali and AU troops last week.
At least 18 civilians were killed and several others wounded in a suicide car bomb attack in Somalia's capital Mogadishu on Saturday. The Al-Shabab militant group said it was behind the attack.
column67: Shabelle Media Network website, Mogadishu, Shabelle Media Network

column63: A renowned Somali elder was killed in a knife attack in the southern port city of Kismayo, witnesses and police said.
A well-known Somali elder has been killed in a drive-by-shooting in Mogadishu on Wednesday.

A member of Somalia's electoral college was shot dead in Adado town, the interim administrative headquarters of Galmudug state. The clan elder, whose name has not been released up till now has been killed by AU soldiers at the entrance of a polling station as he was en route to cast his vote among candidates, sources said.
column72: Curious report: no followup, nor any outrage about the killing being due to AU soldiers; no detail on "sources"

column63: A car bomb has killed at least 25 people and injured 53 others in Somalia's capital, Mogadishu.
column67: Al Jazeera, Deutsche Welle, Shabelle Media Network, Dalsan Radio

column63: Islamist militants have beheaded eight Somali village elders and killed at least seven other people in Galmadug in the Mudug region during fighting spurred by a dispute over payment of an Islamic tax, a villager and a local official said on Wednesday.
column72: Events occurred in five unnamed villages. Could not geolocate Galmadug; coordinates are for Mudug. 10 Shabaab were killed in the fight, so some of the seven "other people" may have been combatants

column63: Unknown assailants have shot and killed a renowned traditional elder in Somali capital, Mogadishu on Tuesday, witnesses and police said.

Five people have been killed and several injured in ethnic clashes between members of the Zaghawa -- the ethnic group of President Idriss Deby and his army officers -- and the Kreda community after a football match in Chad's capital N'Djamena

A car bomb targeting a police station in in the southeastern Turkish city of Diyarbakir has killed nine civilians. The Kurdistan Freedom Hawks (TAK), an offshoot of the outlawed Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) militant group, claimed responsibility.

column28: youth wing of the Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK),
column63: A district governor has died after a bomb attack on his office in the largely Kurdish southeast of Turkey and police have detained 30 people in the investigation, security sources said on Friday. The YPS, a youth wing of the outlawed Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK), claimed responsibility for Thursday's attack in Mardin, according to the ANF news agency, which is close to the militant group. Two other people were wounded in the attack.

column36: individuals associated with Bakonzo tribal king
column63: Human Rights Watch on Wednesday said 141 people, including 15 children, were killed in fierce fighting that erupted late last year in western Uganda between security forces and a tribal king's palace guards.
column72: Ugandan government acknowledges about 100 deaths. The tribal guards were lightly armed (machetes, etc) but 14 police were killed (not included in total) so presumably a number of those remaining deaths were combatants.

column63: More than 20 civilians were killed, and 75 wounded, in the shelling of a busy market in the war-torn Yemeni city of Taiz, including a member of an international aid group, the group and medical officials said on Friday.
Twelve Yemeni civilians were killed and six wounded by a Saudi-led air strike while riding in a pickup truck in the Hiran area of northwest Hajja province early on Wednesday, residents said.
column72: Geonames shows three ""Hiran"" in Hajja; this may or may not be the correct one

column63: Yemeni security and medical officials say at least 13 civilians have been killed by an airstrike by the Saudi-led military coalition in rural areas northeast of Hodeida.
column72: Coordinates for arbitrary location northeast of Hodeida

column13: Lushi, Sakuwa ,Hore Ladde and Garin Dogo
column63: At least 8 people have been killed between Friday and Saturday in clashes between the Fulani and Mummuye ethnic groups in the communities of Lushi, Sakuwa ,Hore Ladde and Garin Dogo in Lau Local Government area of Taraba State North Eastern Nigeria, witnesses say.
The body of the mayor of the southern town of Samayac, was found on the side of a road.
column72: Date is approximate: report on another killing of a mayor on 1-Feb just said ""last week""

column63: A suicide bomber on foot ripped through a crowd of Afghan Supreme Court employees Tuesday, killing at least 20 people and wounding 41 others. The Islamic State claimed responsibility on Wednesday for the attack.

At least six Afghan employees of the International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) were killed on Wednesday near the northern town of Shibirghan, capital of the Jowzjan province, by suspected Islamic State gunmen in northern Afghanistan, officials said. Another two employees were unaccounted for after the attack
Alam Jan Mojahed, a member of [northern] Baghlan Provincial Council has been killed in an ambush by armed men in the Hossain Khel area of Pol-e Khomri city.
An Afghan official says at least 12 civilians were killed and four others wounded when their vehicle struck a roadside bomb in the Urgun district in the eastern Paktika province.

Eleven members of an Afghan family, including women and children, were killed in a grenade attack on their home in in Laghman province's Baad Pakh district, officials said Monday. Three other people were wounded.

Rebels from the Union for Peace in the Central African Republic (UPC), recently executed people in Bakala after calling them to a school for an alleged meeting. Earlier in the day they also killed seven gold miners.
column67: CAJ News Agency, Human Rights Watch
column72: There are at least six "Bakala"s in CAR; this may or may not be the right one. There is also ambiguity on date: one report says this was 12-Dec-2016, though details of the incident are the same.

column63: Three knife-wielding attackers have killed five people and injured ten others in Pishan county in China's far western region of Xinjiang

Three Nigerians and a Cameroon national were among five people killed when gunmen opened fire on a United Nations team in the Hosere Jongbi area near Kontcha, northern Cameroon, on the border between the two countries, the world body said. Several people were also injured in the attack.
column67: Premium Times, Vanguard, Daily Trust, This Day
column72: Could not geolocate Hosere Jongbi area; coordinates are for Kontcha (which is about a kilometer from the border)

column63: Police in southwestern Democratic Republic of Congo on Friday killed at least eight members of Bundu dia Kongo (BDK) as they approached the morgue in the town of Kimpese to recover the bodies of fellow members killed in protests last month, local activists said,
column72: Local activists reported both 8 and 12 deaths; police acknowledged ""several"" people had been killed

column63: Twenty-seven people were killed, five wounded and six others abducted during a massacre perpetrated by suspected Mai-Mai Mazembe in coalition with the Nduma Defence of Congo (NDC-Reformed) led by Guidon on Thursday night [17 February] in the commune of Mutanda, in Rutshuru territory (Nord Kivu).
column72: Possibly this is the same as the attack on the same day on the village of Kyaghala (which couldn't be located), though account is quite different

column63: Militiamen from DR Congo's Nande ethnic group have beheaded 25 Hutu civilians in and around the village of Kyaghala in the country's violence-torn east, a local official said Saturday.
column72: Could not geolocate Kyaghala; coordinates are for location in Nord Kivu in the vicinity of Rutshuru, where another attack was reported around the same time

column63: A radio producer and an announcer have been fatally shot, and one other person injured, in the Dominican Republic while one of them was reading the news during a live transmission on Facebook. Police said the shooting occurred Tuesday in San Pedro de Macoris, just east of the capital of Santo Domingo.

Seven women and three children were killed and 11 people injured when a chieftaincy dispute among members of a traditional ruler's family in the town of Bimbilla in northern Ghana turned violent, police said Friday.

At least five people were killed Monday when police in Conakry, Guinea clamped down on hundreds of students who demonstrated with stones and sticks amid teacher strikes that have kept them out of class for weeks. Hospital officials said 30 people were injured, including members of the security forces

The mayor and a council member of an indigenous village, Rabinal, in northern Guatemala were gunned down Wednesday by unidentified attackers who ambushed the van in which they were traveling, officials said.

A family of five in Honduras' capital was attacked overnight the day after their son, a bus conductor, was murdered after refusing to meet the extortion demands of a gang, relatives and police said Tuesday. Four people were wounded in the attack.
Honduran authorities say a Tolupan indigenous community leader has been shot dead by armed men who barged into his home in the town of Orica, about 75 miles (120 kilometers) northeast of Tegucigalpa.
column72: Reports disagree on exact location: alternative is Montana de La Flor village (which is in the same area)

column63: Twin suicide bombings in Mosul targeting a popular restaurant killed 14 people. The Islamic State group claimed responsibility for the attacks in a statement.

Late Friday, a parked car packed with explosives detonated on a commercial street in the Alam district of the Iraqi capital, Baghdad, killing six civilians and wounding 18, police and hospital officials said.

column36: protesters loyal to Shi'ite cleric Moqtada al-Sadr
column63: At least seven protesters loyal to Shi'ite cleric Moqtada al-Sadr were killed, and 174 others wounded, in clashes that happened Saturday with Iraqi security forces in downtown Baghdad
A suicide bomber detonated a pick-up truck on Wednesday in Sadr City, a heavily populated poor Shi'ite suburb of Baghdad, killing at least 15 and wounding 50, hospital and security sources said.

A car bomb explosion killed 51 people and wounded at least 56 others in southwestern Baghdad on Thursday, a security official told CNN. The blast targeted a busy car market in the predominately Shiite al-Bayaa district of the Iraqi capital, the official said. ISIS claimed responsibility for the bombing in an online statement.
column65: CNN, AFP, BBC, AP, Reuters, NYT
column67: Iraqia News TV, Baghdad, Telegram messaging service in Arabic 1800 gmt 16 Feb 17

column63: Seven people were killed and 14 injured when a car bomb exploded in Al-Amiiryah neighbourhood, western Baghdad
Attackers opened fire on a prison bus near the town of Kalutara outside Colombo on Monday, killing five prisoners and two armed guards in the worst gang-related violence to hit Sri Lanka in decades.

Authorities say a second human rights activist has been killed in the same township in northern Mexico where the first one died two weeks ago. The statement from Chihuahua state prosecutor's office said the body of Juan Ontiveros, a member of the Tarahumara indigenous group, was found Wednesday in Guadalupe y Calvo.
At least 13 people were killed in central Mali at the weekend in inter-ethnic clashes between Fulanis and Bambaras near the town of ke-Macina, the interior ministry said on Monday
column72: Other reports say 30 or 45 killed

column63: Seven people have been killed in attacks by suspected Fulani herdsmen in Bakin Kogi, Goska District of Jama'a Local Government Area in Kaduna State.
Fifteen people have been killed in fresh attacks on four communities by suspected Fulani herdsmen in Atakad District, Kaura Local Government Area in the southern part of Kaduna State.

column39: Bursar of the College of Education (COE)
column63: A former Bursar of the College of Education (COE), Katsina-Ala in Benue State, Mr. Godwin Yanbee Bosua, has been found beaten to death after some unidentified persons allegedly abducted him at the weekend.

A suicide bomber struck police escorting a protest rally in the eastern Pakistani city of Lahore on Monday, killing at least 9 civilians and wounding 87 in an attack claimed by the breakaway Taliban faction Jamat-ul-Ahrar.
column65: BBC, AFP, Reuters, CNN, AP, NYT

column63: An Islamic State suicide bomber struck inside a famed shrine in Sehwan in southern Pakistan on Thursday, killing at least 75 people and wounding more than 150. The Islamic State group claimed the attack in a statement circulated by its Aamaq news agency

According to the district police office , seven people were killed and 20 were injured were as multiple suicide bombers attacked a sessions court in in the Tangi area of Charsadda district on Tuesday. The attack was claimed by the Jamaat-ul-Ahrar (JuA).
A Philippine lawyer who specialized in investigating crimes against the environment has been ambushed and shot dead near her home on the central island of Bohol, police said Friday.

Seven herdsmen were killed in Hijerat near Kadugli in South Kordofan on Friday morning, after which the perpetrators stole dozens of their cows. A witness said the attack was in revenge for earlier theft of cattle from the perpetrators.
column72: Mostly criminal, though this is the sort of thing that can escalate.

column63: Gunmen have shot dead an Elder in Mogadishu on Wednesday night, the latest in a string of targeted assassinations on elders.
Mohamed Omar Hagafey, who served as a spokesman for former Himan and Heeb administration was killed in a drive-by-shooting in Mogadishu on Saturday morning.
A suicide car bomb ripped through a market in Mogadishu on Sunday, killing 39 people and injuring around 50, a local official said.
column65: AFP, BBC, Reuters, CNN, All Africa, AP
column67: Twitter.com in English 1234 gmt 19 Feb 17, Shabelle Media Network, Voice of America, Al Jazeera

column63: Unknown gunmen have shot dead a traditional elder in Mogadishu on Monday evening, the latest in a series of targeted assassinations against elders involved in the recent elections.
Unknown gunmen have shot and killed a senior official working at the office of Somali Parliament speaker office in Mogadishu on Sunday morning.
A witness says senior local government official was killed in a car bomb explosion in Mogadishu on Tuesday morning.

column63: At least 16 people were killed and 44 more wounded Wednesday in two separate attacks in the Afghan capital, police and health officials told CNN

At least eight Afghan civilians, including four children, were killed in a blast as they tried to escape fighting between Afghan forces and the Taliban, officials said Saturday. Some 22 others were injured in the explosion in the Bala Buluk district of Farah province Friday
column72: Some witnesses say explosion was due to Afghan air strike targeting Taliban positions

column40: staff and patients at military hospital
column63: Gunmen dressed as medics attacked a hospital in the Afghan capital on Wednesday and battled security forces for hours, killing more than 49 people and wounding at least 63 in an assault claimed by Islamic State.

An Afghan official says a mortar attack in Khwaja Bahauddin District in northern Takhar province killed five civilians, including four children, all from the same family. Three other people were injured. The Taliban are battling Afghan forces in the region and appear to have been targeting a nearby government position.
column67: Afghan Islamic Press news agency, Peshawar

column63: Jihadists on motorbikes killed two people including a school official early Friday in Kourfayl, a village in Burkina Faso's north, and then went to other villages demanding that schools close, a provincial official said.
column72: Could not geolocate Kourfayl; coordinates are for arbitrary location north of Baraboule, site of earlier attack

column63: Five armed men burst into a small town hospital in Parauapebas in northeastern Brazil's Para State in the Brazilian Amazon, surrounded security guards and shot dead a prominent land rights activist, local media reported on Tuesday

column13: Agoudou Manga, Yasseneme and Ngouyanza villages
column63: At least 50 people have been killed and dozens more injured since Tuesday after armed men attacked Agoudou Manga, Yasseneme and Ngouyanza villages in the central Bambari region of the Central African Republic, local residents who fled their homes told AFP.
column72: Could not geolocate Agoudou Manga, Yasseneme and Ngouyanza villages; coordinates are for Bambari

column63: A traditional Twa chief, his wife and three sons have been shot dead in DRCongo's southeastern Tanganyika Province. The attack occurred on 28 March in Kanambe village which lies about 120 kilometres north of the provincial capital Kalemie.
column72: Could not geolocate Kanambe village; coordinates are for arbitrary location around 120 north of Kalemie

column63: Gunmen from South Sudan have killed 28 people and kidnapped 43 children in neighboring Ethiopia, a government official said on Wednesday. The raids on Sunday and Monday occurred in Gambella's Gog and Jor areas, which border South Sudan's Boma region, said Chol Chany, a regional government spokesman.

A twin suicide bombing struck a village wedding in Hajaj, near the city of Tikrit as the wedding party gathered in the evening hours, killing at least 26 people and wounding at least 63, a government spokesman said Thursday.
Eight people were killed and more than 50 wounded when a car bomb exploded in a crowded street in the Iraqi city of Tikrit on Wednesday, a local official said.

A car bomb blast killed at least 27 people and wounded more than 45 others in a mainly Shi'ite district in southern Baghdad on Monday, police and medical sources said. The Islamic State group has claimed responsibility.

A suicide truck bomb blew up at a checkpoint in the south of the Iraqi capital Baghdad on Wednesday, killing at least 17 civilians and wounding more than 60, police sources said. ISIS issued a statement claiming the attack.

Five people have been killed and six others injured during clashes over cattle grazing rights in the central Kenya region of Isiolo when Somali herders from Auliyan clan in Lagdera attacked Duse village.
column72: Could not geolocate Duse village; coordinates are for arbitrary location in the vicinity of Lagdera; casualty figures in story hard to interpret, and killed may have included two combatants

column63: Thirteen people have been killed and four wounded since Sunday in Kenya's volatile Rift Valley county of Baringo, where a drought has increased cattle rustling, officials said Wednesday. Illchamus herders attacked Pokot herders on Monday in Partololo village, killing two people and stealing 30 cattle, a police spokesman . That triggered a cycle of revenge attacks by both communities on Tuesday.
column72: Could not geolocate Partololo or Mukutani villages; coordinates are for Baringo County

column63: Herders from the Borana and Samburu communities fought a gun battle on Sunday in an area in the centre of I country called Kom, where both groups had taken their livestock to graze, said Charles Ontita, police chief of the town of Isiolo. 11 people were killed and at least two were wounded.

People-smugglers have killed 22 African migrants on from Sabrata beach, 70 kilometres (45 miles) west of Tripoli, a security source said Wednesday. They were killed after refusing to board their boat due to bad weather, the source added. The Libyan Red Crescent confirmed the killings

column36: member of parliament from the Constitutional Union Party
column63: A Moroccan parliamentary member of the liberal Constitutional Union Party was shot and killed in front of his home on Tuesday night in Casablanca,according to a statement from his political party and local media.
on March 2, Cecilio Pineda Birto, a freelancer and the founder of La Voz de Tierra Caliente, was slain at a car wash in Ciudad Altamirano, Guerrero state

Prosecutors said six bodies had been found dumped on Thursday and Friday around the twin resorts of Cabo San Lucas and San Jose del Cabo at the southern tip of the Baja California peninsula, which has been the scene of increasing violence in recent months.
column72: Probably criminal but this area has previously been fairly calm

column63: On March 19, columnist Ricardo Monlui was shot twice as he left a restaurant with his wife and son in Yanga, near the city of Cordoba in the Gulf coast state of Veracruz.

A reporter who investigated drug gangs was found murdered in northern Mexico near the US border on Thursday, police said, the third journalist killed in the country this month. Miroslava Breach, 54, of the newspapers La Jornada and Norte de Juarez, was found dead in her vehicle with multiple gunshot wounds to the head in the city of Chihuahua, police said in a statement.

Mexico's Catholic council of bishops says a priest has been killed in the Pacific coast state of Nayarit. The council identifies Felipe Altamirano Carrillo as an Indigenous priest in the prefecture of Nayar and says he was killed early Monday.
The Police at Force headquarters, yesterday, said that 46 persons were killed and 96 others wounded during the clash that erupted between the Hausa and the Yoruba communities in Ile Ife, Osun State
column67: Leadership, Vanguard, The Guardian, Premium Times

column63: Eight people were killed, while three persons were missing, according to the sole administrator for the council area, Justina Sorkaa, following attacks over the weekend by Fulani herdsmen in Tombo-Mbalagh, Buruku Local Government Area, Benue state
Gunmen yesterday killed the immediate past chairman of Etsako East local government of Edo state, Suleiman Afegbua. Two other people were wounded in the attack.
No fewer than five persons have been reportedly killed in a late night attack on Mbayongo, Nganbeya district of Katsina/Ala Local Government Area of Benue State by unknown armed men.
column72: Motive unclear but seems targeted

column63: Gunmen killed 17 people, mostly women and children, after invading the Zaki Biyam farming community in central Nigeria, police said Tuesday, the latest violence linked to grazing rights disputes. 11 people were wounded in the attack.

The Chairman of the Kaduna State chapter of the Miyetti Allah Cattle Breeders Association of Nigeria (MACBAN), Alhaji Haruna Usman, has alleged that 17 herdsmen have been killed by soldiers in Daile Alkariyo village, Jama'a Local Government Area in the southern part of the state.
Seven people have been killed and at least 18 wounded in a suicide bomb attack in Maidugari in Nigeria's northeastern Borno State.

Pakistani police say gunmen have killed a prominent attorney affiliated with the secular Qaumi Watan political party in Shabqadar. Jamaat-ul-Ahrar, a breakaway faction of Pakistani Taliban militants claimed responsibility for the killing.

A prominent lawyer of Pakistan's minority Ahmadi community and relative of its first Nobel Prize winner was gunned down on Thursday in the town of Nankana in an attack claimed by banned militant group Lashkar-e-Jhangvi.

A bomb apparently targeting a Shiite mosque in Pakistan's northwestern city of Parachinar killed at least 22 people on Friday and wounded at least 90 in an attack claimed by the Pakistani Jamat-ul-Ahrar
At least six people were killed and at least four others wounded when armed militiamen plundered and pillaged the town of Bir Tuwa Shalal, southwest of Fanga in East Jebel Marra on Wednesday.
column72: Could not geolocate Bir Tuwa Shalal or Fanga; coordinates are for arbitrary location in eastern Jebel Marra

column63: Unknown gunmen in Elasha Biyaha on Wednesday evening killed a prominent Somali traditional elder, who was among the delegates elected members of parliament in Adado city, Galmudug state.

A car bomb near a hotel on a busy street in the Somali capital killed at least 13 people and injured 14 on Monday, police and the emergency medical services said. A spokesman for Somali Islamist insurgent group al Shabaab claimed the attack.
Unknown gunmen have shot and killed an Elder who has involved the electoral process in Mogadishu's Bakaro market on Tuesday.

Extremist group Al-Shabaab claimed responsibility for a deadly explosion that police say killed 9 civilians Tuesday afternoon in Mogadishu, Somalia. At least 15 people were injured in the bomb explosion at a busy security checkpoint in the country's capital, according to Somali federal police Maj. Ahmed Ibrahim.
column67: Shabelle Media Network, Dalsan Radio, Al Jazeera
column72: Unusually great diversity in casualty estimates on this one: these figures are from the most detailed report.

column63: Seven aid workers have been killed in an ambush in famine-hit South Sudan, the United Nations said on Sunday. The victims were attacked on Saturday as they travelled from the capital, Juba, to the eastern town of Pibor, according to the UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (OCHA).
column67: Radio Dabanga, Al Jazeera, Deutsche Welle, Capital FM
column72: Coordinates for arbitrary location on road between Juba and Pibor

column39: human rights activist for minority communities
column63: Chaiyaphum Pasae, a campaigner for stateless communities in Thailand's border regions, was shot dead on Friday morning in Chiang Dao district of northern Chiang Mai province after the car he was in was stopped at a military checkpoint. After a public outcry over the incident, the soldier involved in the shooting was charged with "murder while acting in self-defence".

column36: former member of the Russian State Duma
column63: A former lawmaker of the Russian State Duma, Denis Voronenkov, was killed in the centre of the Ukrainian capital of Kiev on Thursday, police said. Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko said on Thursday that the fatal shooting of a former Russian lawmaker in Kiev was an act of Russian "state terrorism".

At least 22 civilians were killed on Friday and dozens wounded when a Saudi-led coalition air strike hit Khokha market in the western province of Hodeida in western Yemen causing a fire to break out, a local official said. A United Nations official confirmed the attack.

At least 42 refugees have been killed and at least and 39 wounded after the boat they were traveling on was fired upon by an unknown helicopter off Yemen's western coast near Hodeida, according to the International Organization for Migration (IOM). Casualties were confirmed by the UNHCR, and the refugees were carrying UNHCR documents.
column65: AP, CNN, Unrecognized, Reuters, NYT, BBC
column67: Deutsche Welle, International Organization for Migration (IOM), UNHCR, Radio Kulmiye website, Mogadishu, Al Jazeera
column72: Arbitrary location in sea near Hodeida

column63: A human rights activist who resides in Nganza Commune in said that in their investigation, it was discovered that at least 148 victims were killed and many others abandoned in their own houses, where some decomposing bodies were found.
column67: Radio Okapi (Goma) in French 0900 gmt 3 Apr 17
column72: Could not unambiguously geolocate Nganza Commune; coordinates are for Kananga. Details are unclear but UN would later report finding at least 40 mass graves in the area (Reuters 19 April 2017 LBA0000020170419ed4j00etd)

column63: A state official in Mexico says a reporter covering the police beat has been shot and killed in La Paz on the Baja California peninsula.

At least nine civilians have been killed when their house collapsed after an Afghanistan army commando unit detonated a cache of ordinance found in the Malgir area of Gereshk district in southern Helmand province.

A suicide attacker detonated explosives Wednesday near major political offices in the Afghan capital of Kabul, killing at least five civilians and injuring 10 others, a spokesman for Afghanistan's Interior Ministry told CNN. ISIS claimed responsibility via a statement released by the group's media wing, Amaq News Agency.

At least 11 civilians were killed when a roadside bomb ripped through their vehicle in the restive southern Afghan province of Helmand, officials said Saturday. The blast occurred when the passengers were travelling from remote Nawa district to the provincial capital Lashkar Gah.
column72: Coordinates are for Nawa district

column63: Two gunmen on a motorcycle drove up to a bar in Jacana, a low-income neighborhood in Sao Paulo, and opened fire, killing seven men and injuring three others.
column67: Folha de Sao Paulo website (www.folha.com.br[http://www.folha.com.br]), Sao Paulo

column63: Hooded gunmen killed nine men in a conflict over territory in remote Taquaru√ßu do Norte in Mato Grosso state on Brazil's border with Bolivia, Brazil's agricultural heartland, government security officials said. The Pastoral Land Commission, which is linked to the Roman Catholic church, called the incident a massacre by big landowners to expel small farmers.
column72: Could not geolocate Taquaru√ßu do Norte; coordinates are for arbitrary location near Bolivian border in Mato Grosso state

column63: Authorities say a brutal armed group loyal to traditional leader Kamwina Nsapu in southern Congo blamed for murdering a U.N. team has killed at least eight people over the weekend in Luebo. Among the victims was the area administrator's wife.

At least 20 people were killed in ethnic clashes last week in Democratic Republic of Congo's troubled Kasai region, according to the United Nations. The UN's DR Congo mission said in a statement on Wednesday that the clashes took place in the central region, east of the Kasai capital, Tshikapa. Violence between members of the Lulua-Luba and Chowe-Pende communities escalated, and saw at least 20 members of the Chowe-Pende killed, the agency said.
column72: Coordinates are for Tshikapa

column63: Twenty-nine people have been killed in three days of clashes between rival factions of a militia group in a village in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo, an official said Friday. The two factions are fighting for control of the village of Bweru.
column72: Probably quite a few are combatants, but some other reports not in our standard set of sources mention civilian casualties as well. "Bwiru" may or may not be the same as "Bweru", which I couldn't locate.

column63: At least 21 people were killed and 59 wounded in Sunday's bomb attack against a Christian Coptic church north of Cairo, the Egyptian health ministry said. The blast took place during a Palm Sunday mass at the Mar Girgis Coptic Church in the city of Tanta. the Islamic State group (IS) has claimed responsibility for the bombing attacks.

Security forces in the Indian-controlled part of Kashmir opened fire Sunday on crowds of people who attacked polling stations in the where voting for a by-election was taking place, killing eight and injuring at least a dozen, officials said. Protesters tried to snatch or damage electronic voting machines in the city of Srinagar.

At least 17 civilians were killed and more than 40 wounded in gun and suicide attacks overnight by Islamic State militants in the northern Iraqi city of Tikrit, security and medical sources said on Wednesday. ISIS claimed responsibility in a statement released on Twitter and tweeted by several ISIS supporters.
column72: 14 police officers also killed, so wounded total probably includes some police

column63: In the Old City of mosul, more than 40 civilians were killed when the militants caught them trying to escape, said a resident of the Farouq district where the symbolic Nuri mosque is located. Another resident of the Old City's Shahwan district said a family of six, including an elderly woman, had also been killed for the same reason.
column72: Date is approximate -- it is the date of the report -- but implication in report is this happened recently

column63: Jihadist militants from the Islamic State group posing as liberating security forces killed at least 15 civilians who welcomed them in central Mosul, officials said Tuesday.

A liberal blogger who wrote satirical critiques of the Maldivian government and the spread of radical Islam died Sunday after being stabbed in the stairway of his apartment building in the capital, Male.

Prosecutors in the small town of Yehualtepec in central Mexico say a man was shot to death by members of a rival clan, and his relatives later went to the other family's house and shot to death five men.

column36: state general secretary of Mexico's leftist Democratic Revolution Party
column63: Gunmen killed the state general secretary of Mexico's leftist Democratic Revolution Party in the state capital, Chilpancingo, in the southern state of Guerrero, authorities said Thursday.

Nine people were killed in what prosecutors said on Sunday was a gun battle between rival drug gangs in an isolated village of the municipality of Churumuco in the mountains of Mexico's west coast state of Michoacan.
No fewer than 15 persons were feared killed when herdsmen attacked farmers in Turan communities in Kwande Local Government Area of Benue State.
Scores of Boko Haram fighters rode on motorcycles into Abbati, a farming community outside Maiduguri, where they killed seven men and stole 360 livestock.
column72: Could not geolocate Abbati; coordinates are for arbitrary location near Maiduguri

column63: Boko Haram jihadists have killed eight loggers near Kayamla village, 10 kilometres from the northeast Nigerian city of Maiduguri, vigilantes and residents told AFP on Sunday.
column72: Could not geolocate Kayamala village; coordinates are for arbitrary location 10 km from Maiduguri

column63: The killing of about 200 pigs by youths in Kafinkoro village, Paikoro Local Government Area of Niger State, reportedly led to a violent clash that resulted in the death of five women who were raising pigs.
column72: The pig-killers were probably Moslem and the pig-farmers Christian, though article doesn't say so explicitly

column63: No fewer than 13 persons were reportedly killed at the weekend in Asso village, Jama'a Local Government Area in the southern part of Kaduna State after suspected herdsmen attacked the community. In addition to the dead, four persons sustained gunshot wounds.

column36: Transition Secretary of the Ukanafun Local Government Area
column63: The Transition Secretary of the Ukanafun Local Government Area of Akwa Ibom State, Mr. Ime Atakpa, has been assassinated by unknown gunme

The custodian of a local Sufi shrine and his accomplices killed 20 devotees after intoxicating them in Sargodha, about 105 miles northwest of Lahore in eastern Punjab province, police said Sunday, in what officials said was the outcome of a dispute over custodianship of the shrine. Three additional people were injured in the attack.
column72: Other reports say custodian had serious mental issues, though he allegedly had 4 accomplices.

column63: At least 13 people were killed, including women and children, and 9 others injured when a passenger vehicle struck a roadside bomb in the Godar area of Kurram tribal district in Pakistan's northwest tribal region bordering Afghanistan on Tuesday, officials said. The attack was claimed by both Jamat-ul-Ahrar and and the Islamic State group (IS), and the victims were Shia

Fifteen people were killed in Monday's blast on a metro train in St Petersburg and 47 people have been injured, Russian news agency Interfax reported. Authorities say the attack was carried out by 22-year-old suicide bomber Akbarjon Djalilov, a Russian national born in Kyrgyzstan.
column72: No clear connection to a group

column63: Clashes between Arab Maaliya and Rizeigat tribes, sparked by a livestock theft, in Sudan's conflict-hit East Darfur state killed at least nine people (mostly Rizeigat) and injured four on Saturday in and around Rizeigat village, tribal leaders told AFP.
column72: Not sure if 'Rizeigat' is really the name of the village; later story puts it at 'El Khamsat' but that can't be geolocated.

column63: At least eight people were killed and 10 wounded on Wednesday when a car bomb exploded at a restaurant near the Somali ministry of internal security in Mogadishu, officials said.
column65: Reuters, BBC, AP, AFP, All Africa

column63: A Somali member of parliament says African Union forces (AMISOM) killed five members from the same family near the coastal town of Barawe in Somalia's southern Lower Shabelle region.
At least 14 people were killed and seven injured when the minibus they were travelling in hit a landmine near Golweyn in the southern Somali region of Lower Shebelle, police said.

A car bomb targeting senior officials leaving a military base in Mogadishu destroyed a minibus carrying civilians, with at least ten civilians killed, the Somali military said on Sunday, an attack claim by Islamist al Shabaab militants.
column65: BBC, Reuters, AFP, All Africa, CNN, AP

column63: At least five people, including four children, were reported to have been killed, and seven wounded in mortar shells fired into homes in the Somali capital of Mogadishu on Tuesday afternoon, witnesses said.
Unidentified gunmen have shot and killed a prominent Somali elder in the northern divided city of Galkayo, the regional capital of Mudug region on Wednesday night.
South Sudanese army soldiers killed as many as 17 people in the town of Parjok near the Ugandan border, witnesses said.
column72: Government confirms incident occurred, says victims were 'bandits'

column63: At least 16 civilians were killed on Monday in the South Sudanese city of Wau, according to the United Nations' peacekeeping mission in the country (UNMISS), with witnesses reporting that government-aligned militia were targeting residents based on their ethnic group.
column67: Al Jazeera, UN peacekeeping mission, CAJ News Agency

column63: At least 14 people were killed in the South Sudanese town of Raga when fighting erupted between government forces and the main rebel group, a rebel spokesman said on Saturday, mentioning only one soldier killed. The UN confirmed the fighting but did not have details.
column72: Probably some additional combatants in the total but details were vague

column63: Eighteen people -- seven herders and 11 of the raiders -- have been killed in a cattle raid in in Paloch County of Western Lakes State in central South Sudan, privately-owned National Courier website is reporting on its official Facebook page.
column72: Could not geolocate Paloch County; coordinates are for arbitrary location in Western Lakes state

column13: 60 kilometres (37 miles) north of the capital N'Djamena
column63: Around 10 Chadian troops who had been detained have been killed during an attack on their convoy while they were being taken to prison, government sources said Wednesday, while dozens of prisoners escaped. Unknown assailants struck the convoy aboard "high-powered" vehicles 60 kilometres (37 miles) north of the capital N'Djamena overnight and singled out individuals to be killed.
column72: Arbitrary location on highway about 60 km north of N'Djamena

column39: dissident Iranian television executive and business partner
column63: A dissident Iranian television executive was assassinated in Istanbul on Saturday evening, months after he was sentenced in absentia to a six-year prison term by an Iranian court for spreading propaganda. The victim's Kuwaiti business partner was also killed in the attack.
column72: Victim was apparently involved in a number of financial disputes, so killing may not have been political

column63: Yemeni security and tribal officials say two airstrikes in the Sarawah district suspected to be by the Saudi-led coalition fighting rebels have killed eight people, including two women and several paramedics. Three more people were wounded.
column72: There are two ""Sarawah""s in adjacent provinces (Ibb is the other); this may or may not be the right one

column63: The Provincial Gang Investigation Unit is investigating a case of murder after five people were shot and killed in a shack in Mistletoe Road In Ext 33 in Bethelsdorp last night, 29 April 2017.
An Afghan official says a bombing at a religious school in Charikar in northern Parwan province has killed the chief cleric and wounded four students.

The locals, who witnessed an explosion in a Shia-populated area in Herat Province on 12 May, say a motorbike laden with explosives was the cause of the blast on 12 May which killed six people and wounded 17 others in western Herat city, not a gas cylinder, which provincial officials have claimed. According to the local residents, a number of steel items and a remote controller have been discovered from the site of the incident, and an Islamic State affiliate claimed credit for the attack.
An Afghan official and relatives say five children playing with an unexploded mortar round were killed in Laghman province in eastern Afghanistan.

column63: Eleven members of an Afghan family, mostly women and children, were killed Friday when their vehicle hit a roadside bomb while they were travelling for an engagement ceremony in the country's volatile east. The attack occurred in the Mohammad Agha district of Logar province

column67: Radio France Internationale in French 18 May 17

column63: Five people were killed in Bahrain on Tuesday after the police raided a protest by supporters of a top cleric in the Shiite village of Diraz, near the capital of Manama, the interior ministry said.

column67: Radio France Internationale website, Paris, Al Jazeera

In Cote d'Ivoire, six people have been killed near the town of Arrah by security officers who were hunting down suspected armed robbers and opened fire on a hearse. Five funeral home workers and a passerby died. Four gendarmes and their commander were arrested.

column28: Militia fighters loyal to Kamwina Nsapu

column63: At least 28 people have been killed in Egypt after unidentified gunmen opened fire on a bus carrying Coptic Christians on a road to the St. Samuel the Confessor monastery in Maghagha. column67: Facebook in Arabic 1130 gmt 26 May 17, Telegram messaging service in Arabic 1134 gmt 27 May 17

column63: Two suicide car bombs in southwestern Baghdad killed 7 civilians, and wounded at least 20 late on Friday night, according to Iraqi police and hospital officials.
ISIS has claimed responsibility for a rare attack in the southern Iraqi city of Basra, which local officials said killed at least 35 civilians and security personnel, and wounded at least 30 more.
column67: Telegram messaging service in Arabic 1828 gmt 19 May 17

column67: Amaq news agency in Arabic 0900 gmt 30 May 17, Shafaq News website, Baghdad, Telegram messaging service in Arabic 30 May 17

column72: Figure for wounded probably includes security personnel

column63: Suspected Al Shabaab militants attacked a village in Mandera and killed a chief. The incident occurred at Omar Jillo in Lafey sub-County.

A car bomb killed a prominent tribal elder allied to eastern security forces and five other people outside a mosque in Suluq, 31 miles (50 km) south of Benghazi as they were leaving afternoon prayers on Friday, a security official said. 11 people were wounded in the attack.

Armed gunmen shot and killed a prominent Mexican activist dedicated to searching for "disappeared" persons in the municipality of San Fernando in the northern state of Tamaulipas, authorities said on Thursday.
Mexican journalist Javier Valdez C√°rdenas, who reported extensively on drug trafficking, was killed on Monday in Culiac√°n in Sinaloa, officials said.

N ational, state and local officials warned the Mexican government of increasing violence and the need for extra security in the state of Jalisco, where two indigenous brothers, both members of the Huichol tribe and leaders in a battle for restitution of indigenous land from local ranchers, were shot dead in the Huichol territory of San Sebastian Teponahuaxtl√°n and Tuxpan de Bola√±os.

Borno state police spokesman Murtala Ibrahim said two women with explosives strapped to their bodies blew themselves up in the Konduga area on Thursday night, "killing themselves and five other people, including a child". Six people were injured in the attack.

No fewer than 15 persons have been reportedly killed in a fresh attack on Tse-Akaa, Mba'abaji and Tse-Orlalu villages in Logo Local Government Area of Benue State by suspected herdsmen Sunday evening.
Boko Haram jihadists have killed six farmers who were working on their land near the northeast Nigerian city of Maiduguri, civilian militia members and locals told AFP on Monday.

Gunmen believed to be Fulani cattle herders killed 27 farmers praying inside a mosque over a land dispute in central Nigeria, a police spokesman told AFP Monday. The attack happened at about 05:00 a.m. (0400 GMT) on Saturday at Epogi community, in the Mokwa LGA, Niger State. Five other people were injured.
Unknown gunmen killed a family of six-- husband, wife and four children-- in a pre-dawn attack at their home in the Atiba area of Odogbolu Local Government Area of Ogun State.

In Tunga Malam Village, a cattle market not too far from Paiko, the headquarters of Paikoro Local Government Area, when five persons were killed in cold blood over an undisclosed disagreement between a villager and Fulani man.
column72: Ethnic identities of perpetrators and victims ambiguous in the report

column63: Over 11 persons have been killed, scores injured, and 15,000 others displaced in the herdsmen and farmers' clash in Bali Local Government Area of Taraba State.

Police in Bayelsa State have confirmed that suspected assassins have stabbed to death Pamo Hobobo, a former acting chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) ‚Äéin the state. The victim was attacked in his house at Yenizue-Gene in Yenagoa Local Government Area.
Witnesses said the remains of five locals identified as IDPs were on Monday found a day after suspected Boko Haram attacked and beheaded them in Nguro village in Konduga local government area.
Five persons have so far lost their lives in Nteje, Anambra State over protracted land dispute in the community.

Backed by artillery, Afghan security forces fired across the border on Pakistani census workers and troops escorting them on Friday in the border town of Chaman in southwestern Baluchistan province, killing nine civilians, Pakistan said. 42 people were wounded in the attack.
column72: Two Afghan civilians were killed and 23 wounded in Pakistani retaliatory fire

column63: At least 25 people were killed and 30 others were wounded when the convoy of a senior Pakistani politician was hit by a bomb in Mastung, a remote district in Baluchistan Province. on Friday, officials said. Through its Syria-based Amaq news agency, the Islamic State claimed responsibility for the attack.
A Pakistani official says gunmen have killed 10 laborers who were working on a road project near the recently completed Gwadar port in Baluchistan province, which was built with Chinese funding.
Islamist militants locked in street-to-street battles with security forces in the southern Philippine city of Marawi have killed 19 civilians, the military said Sunday

Prison officers in Papua New Guinea shot and killed 17 inmates involved in a mass prison break from the Buimo prison in the city of Lae on Papua New Guinea's north coast, local media reported on Monday

Five civilians were killed and seven wounded by government Rapid Support Forces (RSF) in a raid on the rebel-held Ein Siro area near Kutum that witnessed renewed fighting between paramilitary forces and armed rebels on Sunday.

A suicide bomber rammed a car laden with explosives into a cafe in central Mogadishu on Monday, killing at least eight people and wounding 10 in an attack claimed by the Islamist militant group al Shabaab.
Gunmen believed to be Al Shabaab members have shot and killed a well-known Somali elder in Mogadishu on Wednesday morning, witnesses said.
The Islamic State group has claimed its first suicide attack in Somalia, which police said Wednesday killed five people at a checkpoint in the northeastern port city of Bosaso.

At least six people were killed and nine others injured when the Air and Duduble sub-clans started fighting early Saturday morning in Labi-Aano village, 45 km east of Dhuusamareeb, residents and community elders said on Saturday.
column72: Could not geolocate Labi-Aano village; coordinates are for the only village I could find using Google satellite view about 45 km east of Dhuusamareeb

column63: A car bomb exploded in Somalia's capital, killing at least eight people and injuring 15, police said Wednesday, as the extremist group al-Shabab quickly claimed responsibility.
A gunman has shot dead six people and wounded 15 at a camp for the displaced in the town of Abud Wak in Galgudud Region in central Somalia.
An electoral delegate has been shot and killed by two men armed with pistols at Khat market in Mogadishu's Hodon district, according to a witness.

A strike on a vehicle by the Saudi-led coalition intervening in Yemen killed 23 civilians on Wednesday, including women and children, in Mouza near the southwestern city of Taez, Shiite Huthi rebels said. A military source with loyalist forces confirmed the raid, saying 20 civilians had died, and said it appeared to have been the result of a "mistake".
column67: BBC Monitoring in Arabic 1310 gmt 18 May 17

column63: A suicide attack on a Shi'ite mosque in the western Afghan city of Herat killed more than 29 people and wounded more than 64 on Tuesday, officials said. Islamic State has claimed responsibility the attack.

column63: Islamic State group (IS) has belatedly claimed involvement in an offensive targeting a Shia village of Mirzawalang in Sayad district of Sar-e Pul province in northern Afghanistan in which at least 62 civilians were confirmed killed according to government figures.

column63: A suicide bomber blew himself up at the entrance to a Shi'ite Muslim mosque in Kabul as other attackers stormed the building, killing at least 27 civilians and wounding at least 22, including worshippers gathering for Friday prayers, officials said. Islamic State claimed responsibility.

A suicide bomber blew himself up at a bank close to the heavily protected U.S. embassy in the Afghan capital Kabul on Tuesday, killing at least five people and wounding eight, the interior ministry said. The Taliban claimed responsibility for the attack.

Eighteen people have been killed and nine wounded in a jihadist attack on a Turkish restaurant in Burkina Faso's capital Ouagadougou frequented by tourists and other foreigners, the government said Monday.
Ten people were killed in a southern village near Alindao on August 4, according to OCHA
Fighting in Ngaoundaye, near the borders with Cameroon and Chad, killed at least 10 and forced around 7,000 people to flee the area, several sources told AFP.
column72: Date is unclear

column63: Clashes between a militia and a self-defense group in Gambo in southeastern Central African Republic have left at least 30 civilians dead including six Red Cross volunteers who were attending a crisis meeting at a health facility, officials said Wednesday.

A suicide bomber has killed at least eight people and wounded 4 in the village of Ouro-Kessoum, two kilometres from the Nigerian border, in Cameroon's Far North region, a local official and a military source said on Sunday. The attack occurred on Saturday near Amchide in Cameroon's Far North region

Fifteen people were shot dead in an overnight attack in north Cameroon, blamed on Boko Haram Islamists, a security source said Friday. The attack happened in the town of Gakara close to the Nigerian border.

On Friday, a group of Twa pygmies attacked the Luba, a Bantu ethnic group, near Kalemi, in Tanganyika province, the aid workers said. "According to information gathered, there were about 50 deaths in the attack on the group," Ilunga Musafiri, president of the local NGO Inter-church Council said.

Twelve people were killed Monday by stray gunfire in a wave of violence in Kinshasa, a spokesman for the national police said, accusing the Bundu Dia Mayala political-religious sect opposed to President Joseph Kabila.

column63: University student activist Vladimir Lantigua was shot and killed Tuesday by police during a protest in San Francisco de Macoris calling for more spending on infrastructure and demanding the prosecution of a former city official accused of corruption.
column72: Unclear the extent to which the activist was deliberately targeted; police deny responsibility

column63: 16 people were killed and at least 120 injured Thursday when a driver deliberately slammed a van into crowds on Barcelona's most popular street in what police said was a ""terror attack"" by local Islamic extremists.
Five civilians including two children were killed and 12 injured in a gang shooting to free an imprisoned gang member in a hospital in Guatemala City on Wednesday, officials said.

At least 36 people were killed and at least 120 injured Friday and Saturday when clashes broke out in then northern India city of Panchkula after a court convicted a controversial religious leader of raping two of his followers, sparking fury among tens of thousands of supporters who had gathered to await the verdict.
column72: Some casualties may be due to the protestors, though reports don't say this directly

column63: Mainstream media outlets reported that at least five civilians had been killed in two separate car bomb explosions in Shiite neighborhoods southern Baghdad. The Islamic State claimed responsibility for the attacks.
column67: Amaq news agency in Arabic 1315 gmt 27 Aug 17

column67: Amaq news agency in Arabic 1315 gmt 27 Aug 17, Amaq news agency in Arabic 1045 gmt 28 Aug 17

column63: Authorities in the western Mexico state of Durango say a preliminary investigation suggests a weekend shootout near San Jose de Viborillas that killed 10 people was the result of a long-running feud between families.

Nine inmates were killed Thursday as gang members stabbed and bludgeoned their rivals to death in a prison brawl in Mexico, authorities said. The fight broke out at a prison in Reynosa, a city near the US border in the northeastern state of Tamaulipas. Two inmates were wounded

A newspaper reporter in the Mexican Gulf coast state of Veracruz who was enrolled in a government protection program for journalists was killed Tuesday along with two other men longside the highway in Hueyapan, one of his editors and a journalist advocacy group said.
column72: Government claims killing was incidental and the targets were the other two people killed

column63: Suspected insurgents killed at least six members of a Buddhist ethnic minority near the town of Maungdaw in western Myanmar on Thursday, the government and regional sources said, amid spiralling violence in troubled Rakhine state.
Authorities in northern Nigeria say Boko Haram extremists have killed at least seven people in an attack on Mildu village near the town of Madagali where they burned homes and shops to the ground.
column72: Curiously, no information on LGA

column63: Gunmen killed 11 people and wounded 18 others in a church in southeastern Nigeria on Sunday in an attack arising from a feud between members of the local community, officials said. The attack occurred in Ozubulu in Ekwusigo Local Government Area of Anambra State.
column65: AFP, All Africa, AP, Reuters, NYT
column72: Numerous accounts indicate target was a local drug lord (who was not present) and perpetrators were from a rival gang

column63: Boko Haram militants killed at least 30 fishermen in in a series of raids between Saturday and Monday at villages around Lake Chad near the northeast Nigerian border town of Baga in northeastern Nigeria, the governor of Borno state, residents and military sources said on Tuesday.
Five alleged kidnappers were lynched by a mob early Monday morning in Tella town of Gassol Local Government Area of Taraba state

the Borno State Commissioner of Police has confirmed the killing of 16 people in Konduga LGA, while 82 others were injured when a suicide bomber sneaked into a Market square in Mandarari village of Konduga Local Government Area.
column72: Other reports say 20 or 30 people killed

column63: Boko Haram jihadists killed at least 12 people and injured four in Kijimatari, a village in Guzamala LGA northeast Borno state on Tuesday in what appeared to be a targeted reprisal attack on alleged informers.

Boko Haram fighters entered villages in the Nganzai area on Wednesday, slitting throats and using guns to kill at least 15 people while injuring two others, said Modu Jialta, a member of a local self-defense group. The attackers also burned homes.
Thursday insurgents attacked and killed 17 farmers at Bula Buba and Tawarmada village, some five kilometres away from Damboa town.

A suicide bomber riding a motorcycle rammed into a military truck near a busy bus station in southwestern Pakistan, killing at least sevne civilians and eight soldiers, and wounding at least 40 others, military officials said on Sunday. The Islamic State group claimed responsibility for the attack.
column67: Telegram messaging service in Arabic 2029 gmt 12 Aug 17

column63: Philippine police said Wednesday that an updated report shows anti-drug operations in various parts of Bulacan province this week left 32 alleged drug offenders dead
column72: No indications that victims were shooting at police

column72: No indications that victims were shooting at police

column63: Islamist Abu Sayyaf gunmen killed nine people and injured ten others as they attacked in the town of Maluso in the Philippines at dawn Monday, burning houses in which women and children were sleeping, police said.
At least five people were killed and more than a dozen injured in a deadly suicide car bomb explosion in Somalia's southern port city of Kismayo on Tuesday afternoon

A U.N. official in South Sudan's capital Juba, told Reuters they had received reports on Saturday that 25 civilians had been killed and 27 wounded in Gok state's Cueibet county in clashes between Waat and Ayiel, two ethnic groups that are part of South Sudan's Dinka Gok tribe. A legislator from Gok state confirmed the report.
A prominent conservationist who worked on high profile ivory smuggling cases has been shot dead in Tanzania, colleagues said on Tuesda

Thirty-seven inmates were killed during an overnight raid by government security forces on a prison in the state capital Puerto Ayacucho in Venezuela's southern jungle state of Amazonas, the governor said on Wednesday.
column72: Some reports call the situation a ""riot"" so some of the prisoners may have killed by other prisoners. Others just blame government

column63: At least eight people were killed and 21 were injured during a shootout between criminal gangs that took place in Ciudad Bolivar in the southeastern Venezuelan state of Bolivar

Three women and six children from the same family were killed in an air strike by the Saudi-led coalition on their home in the Muhaddah district on the south-western outskirts of Saada city in northern Yemen on Friday. Five other members of the family were injured.
column67: BBC Monitoring in Arabic 1535 gmt 5 Aug 17

column63: A bomb went off on Monday at a busy market in the southern Yemeni city of Qaataba in Dhale province in southern Yemen on Monday killed 12 civilians and wounded four.
At least 51 people were killed Wednesday in an airstrike that hit a hotel on the outskirts of Sanaa, Yemen's capital, officials and local medics said. At least 26 people were reported injured.

An air raid struck a building in Yemen's capital on Friday, killing at least 14 people, six of them children, when an adjacent apartment block collapsed, residents said. The Saudi-led Arab military coalition on Saturday admitted responsibility, describing it as a "technical mistake".
Witnesses say an airstrike by the Saudi-led coalition battling Shiite rebels in Yemen has struck a checkpoint near the capital, killing at least five civilians.

In the small Hindu village in Kha Maung Seik in northern Rakhine state, where Myanmar authorities have exhumed 45 corpses from mass graves since Sunday. The army says these are evidence of a massacre by Muslim Rohingya militants on August 25 which was reported by civilian eyewitnesses

column63: In Bria at least seven people have been killed in the villages of Boungou and Ngoungoa.
A girl with a bomb strapped to her walked into a mosque in northern Cameroon where it exploded, killing five worshippers at the Sanda-Wadjiri mosque in remote Kolofata.
Five people have been killed in a twin suicide attack in Kossa in Cameroon's Far North Region, the privately-owned L'Oeil du Sahel newspaper has reported.

At least 34 refugees who had fled political violence in Burundi were killed and 117 wounded by government forces in Kamanyola in the neighboring Democratic Republic of Congo, a civil society group said Saturday. column72: Coordinates are for Guji Zone

The Ethiopian Social Democratic Party said six people were killed and about 5,000 displaced in ethnic clashes on the border between Bale and Sidama zones in Oromiya and SNNPS, respectively.
Gauri Lankesh, the editor of a weekly and a fierce critic of Hindu hard-liners, was shot and killed outside her home in Bangalore on Sept. 5.
A reporter covering political unrest in India's northeast was beaten to death during violent clashes outside Agartala, the capital of remote Tripura state.
Eighty-four people were killed and 93 people were injured in the attack in Nasiriyah targeting a restaurant frequented by Shiite Muslim pilgrims. ISIS claimed responsibility.

column63: Two tribal leaders and two other men were killed when their car was riddled with bullets Friday as they returned from a mediation mission Mizda in central Libya, local sources said.
Anti-crime groups in Mexico are mourning the shooting death of a businessman and anti-crime activist in Villahermosa in the southern Gulf coast state of Tabasco.
Five people were killed and two injured in a shooting at a bar in the central Mexican city of Irapuato, a Guanajuato state official said Wednesday.
Suspected Boko Haram militants killed 18 people in a displaced persons camp in Banki on Nigeria's border with Cameroon on Friday, according to local witnesses and officials
The leader of a self-defense group in northern Nigeria says suspected Boko Haram insurgents have killed at least nine people in two nights of raids at a farm near Gongulong outside Maiduguri city.
19 people were reportedly attacked and killed by suspected Fulani herdsmen in Ancha, a village in Maingo, Bassa Local Government Area of Plateau State on Thursday night. Five people were injured

Boko Haram fighters killed nine farmers from a displaced persons camp near Rann, an aid worker and a resident said on Friday.

A female suicide bomber killed five people and injured three on Tuesday when she blew herself up in a mosque in the town of Dikwa, 90 kilometres (60 miles) from Maiduguri in northeast Nigeria, in the latest attack blamed on Boko Haram jihadists, local militiamen told AFP.

At least six Pakistani villagers were killed and 26 were wounded in an overnight attack by India on the Charwah and Harpal villages, Punjab province, in the disputed Himalayan region of Kashmir, Pakistan's military said Friday

Six farmers were shot dead in the Peruvian Amazon near the native Shipibo community of Santa Clara de Uchunya in the region of Ucayali by a group of masked men in an apparent dispute over land rights, a police officer and a tribal leader said on Thursday.
Two well-known elders were reported to have been killed in El Wak, a town near Somali border with Kenya on Friday night, residents said.
An al Shabaab bomb attacknear the khat market of Af-Urur, , 100 km (60 miles) south of the city of Bossaso, killed 7 civilians in Somalia's Puntland region on Friday, the Puntland military said.
